title: savory ham and rice
directions: Combine carrots, onions, green pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer (covered) for 5 minutes.
Do not drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: frozen fudge pops
directions: Mix pudding, sugar and milk; cook.
Stir over medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir. Pour into a shallow pan.
Freeze until ice crystals form around edges (about 30 minutes).
Stir until smooth but not melted, then spoon into molds.
Freeze until firm.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Line bottom of greased casserole with half the bread; add half the cheese.
Sprinkle with half the salt and half the mustard. Repeat layers.
Dot with butter.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place casserole in pan of water.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: roast - crock-pot style
directions: Line bottom of crock-pot with sliced onion. Salt and pepper roast and put into pot.
Pour can of soup over roast.
Pour additional water until 1/2 to 3/4-inches below top of roast. Cover and cook 7 to 10 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, corn syrup and butter.
Add milk; stir and boil until it forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Turn off stove and add vanilla and peanut butter and pour onto a greased plate.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix together the pineapple and pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip. Blend well and mix with first 3 ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Tear bread in pieces into a large mixing bowl; add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Form lightly into loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Spread 3 tablespoons catsup over top of loaf before baking.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally on low heat.

title: pineapple congealed salad
directions: Blend in blender until smooth, cream cheese, Crisco oil and sugar.
Stir in crushed pineapple.

title: water chestnuts
directions: Wrap water chestnuts in piece of bacon; secure with toothpick. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Drain grease.

title: crescent ham roll
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Separate dinner rolls into 2 rectangles. Press edges together. Spread ham, cheese and olives on one rectangle. Place other rectangle over this and press edges together with fork. Beat egg and brush over top. Sprinkle sesame seeds on top. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Slice thin.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add peeled onion and thinly sliced pepper.
Cook over low flame 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook slowly for 1 hour.
After the rice absorbs the moisture, stir to prevent burning.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook and rinse noodles and coat with oil. Mix rest of ingredients and add to noodles. Other options to add 1 can pimento, green peppers, tomatoes, onion, broccoli or cucumbers.

title: manicotti
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1-quart casserole; add onion and garlic.
Microwave at High 2 1/2 to 4 minutes, or until no longer pink.
Break up meat; drain.
Combine in medium bowl, Ricotta, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, 4 tablespoons Parmesan, eggs, parsley, salt, basil, oregano and pepper.
Set aside.
Stir spaghetti sauce into beef.
Cover.
Microwave at High 1 1/4 to 3 minutes until hot, stirring after half the time.
Stuff manicotti with Ricotta mixture while microwaving sauce.
Spread small amount of sauce in 12 x 8-inch dish.
Place manicotti side by side in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High 11 to 16 minutes or until thoroughly heated, rotating dish after half the cooking time.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Parmesan over top.
Cover.
Let stand 3 minutes.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Coat fish fillets with squeeze margarine.
Use shaker bag to coat fish with fish fry mix.
Place on greased baking dish. Squeeze small amounts of margarine on each piece of fish.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: fig preserves
directions: Sort figs to use those of even ripeness.
Sprinkle soda over figs.
Cover with boiling water and let stand about 15 minutes. Drain and rinse well, the last time, in warm water.
Dissolve sugar in cup of water.
Add figs and lemon and cook slowly (simmer), partly covered (wipe moisture from lid) until clear.
Resterilize jars.
Process 20 minutes in hot water.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Layer strips of tortillas and other ingredients in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Last layer should be tortillas.
Sprinkle with lots of grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: slow cooker apple butter
directions: Peel and prepare the applesauce.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put in slow cooker on high and stir occasionally. (It may be cooked on low if you will not be there to stir.)
Cook without lid.
Apple butter is done when a small amount placed on a saucer does not form juice around it.
It should look nice and deep in color.
Put into jars and seal.
For thinner texture, do not cook too long.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: 1. Peel the potatoes and chop them into bite-size pieces- you should have about 4 C. Make sure the celery and onion are minced into very small pieces about the size of a grain of rice. The carrot be grated, not shredded.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: This is a make ahead salad that keeps well.

title: desperation steak
directions: Remove bone from steak; pound well.
Make rectangle.
Spread with layer of onion and sour cream mix.
Pat thin layer of sausage over all.
Mix dressing according to package.
Pat over sausage. Start on long side.
Roll up; hold with toothpicks.
Put seam side down.
Spread onion and sour cream mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Good for unexpected company.

title: jack's macaroni and cheese
directions: Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and salt.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Fold cheese sauce into macaroni in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain and squeeze dry.

title: spinach dip
directions: Do not cook spinach.
Drain spinach and press between 2 paper towels.
Mix all other ingredients.
Serve with pita bread or crackers.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper and pour in greased pie dish over all other ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Cool slightly, cut into pie shaped servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until light.
Sift and add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda, then add vanilla, apples and nuts. Lightly grease and flour two loaf pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: no sugar apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice concentrate in saucepan. Add apple slices. Cover and simmer until tender (only takes a few minutes). Stir in tapioca. Add cinnamon. Simmer until mixture begins to thicken. Pour filling into unbaked pie shell. Dot with margarine. Cover with pastry top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake just until silver knife inserted 1-inch from side comes out clean.
The center may still look soft but will set later. Bake in 450° oven for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: indoor smores
directions: Grease rectangular pan.
Heat corn syrup, butter and chocolate morsels to boiling in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over cereal in large mixing bowl; toss quickly until completely coated with chocolate.
Fold in marshmallows, one cup at a time.
Press mixture evenly in pan with piece of wax paper.
Let stand until firm, at least 1 hour.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: monster toast
directions: Pour a small amount of milk in several cups.
Add food coloring to make bright colors.
Use clean paint brushes to paint a monster face on some bread.
Toast the bread.
Butter lightly and eat!

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan (metal or glass).
Break up lettuce; spread over bottom of pan.
Spread onion slices; sprinkle celery pieces over onion.
Break up and spread box of frozen peas. Spread salad dressing over all; top with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Cover; chill overnight.

title: lemon cookies baked in a waffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set overnight.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into a waffle pan.
Close lid and cook like a waffle until lightly golden in color.
Let cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and spices into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs, applesauce and nuts.
Beat until well blended.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoons about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet immediately and cool.
Makes about 3 dozen medium size.
May be baked as cake in 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together. Pour half of the cornbread mixture in a greased iron skillet. Layer in meat, cheese and onions. Pour remaining cornbread mixture on top and spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: pasta with peas and sausage
directions: This recipe doesn't need any measuring.
Use as much or as little as you like.
Prepare pasta according to package directions.
Brown the Italian sausage (mixture of mild and spicy is nice) and drain.
While pasta is still boiling, add peas.
When pasta is al dente; drain.
Mix pasta/peas, meat and sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with a nice salad and bread. Other items that you could add to this dish are diced tomatoes or chopped spinach.

title: kentucky fruit cake
directions: Combine raisins, water and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add butter; set aside to cool.
Combine fruit and add 1/2 cup flour; dredge.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine all dry ingredients and mix.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 275° in oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon bars
directions: Beat butter on high speed for 30 to 45 seconds. Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until well mixed. Beat in 1 cup of flour until crumbly. press mixture in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 14 to 18 minutes (until golden). Beat eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, lemon zest, lemon juice and baking powder for 2 minutes. Pour over crust. Bake at 325° for 22 to 25 minutes until golden around edges and center is set. Cool on wire rack. Sift powdered sugar and cut into 20 bars.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add oatmeal.
Press in greased jelly roll pan.

title: cheese cream brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Stir and cool.
Cream 2 tablespoons of margarine with cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add 1 egg, 1 tablespoon of flour and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat 2 eggs until light.
Slowly beat in 1 cup of sugar.
Add baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spread 1/2 batter in a greased 8 or 9-inch square pan. Top with cream cheese mixture.
Spoon rest of chocolate mixture over top.
Zigzag with knife through batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until done, but moist.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Break up real good and pour Kahlua over it.
Cover.
Let stand 8 hours. Make pudding as directed and Dream Whip according to Dream Pie directions on box; set aside.
Use a trifle bowl.
Add 1 layer of cake and Kahlua, 1 layer Dream Pie mix, 1 layer chocolate pudding, 1 layer Cool Whip and 1 layer of crushed Heath bars.
Keep layering until all is used.
Keep in icebox until ready to serve.

title: cheesy bacon stuffed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in microwave until done.
Cut lengthwise, remove pulp and save shell.
Combine remaining ingredients with cooked potatoes.
Stuff shells with potato mixture.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky Way bars and one stick butter; set aside.
Cream sugar and one stick butter.
Add eggs mixing well.
Combine flour and soda and sift.
Add flour mixture and buttermilk to sugar and butter; mix well.
Add candy and butter.
Stir in chopped pecans. Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: pecan squares
directions: Mix shortening and sugar, then add beaten egg.
Mix pecans and flour together, covering the pecans with the flour.
Then mix the pecan-flour to the other mixture.
Pour in greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pinch-me-cake
directions: Mix yeast in warm water; scald milk (cool).
Add shortening, milk, sugar, beaten eggs and salt.
Add flour gradually.
Let rise 2 hours.
Melt a stick of butter.
Put 1 1/2 cups sugar with 4 tablespoons cinnamon in bowl.
After 2 hours or rising, punch dough down.
Pinch pieces of dough off; roll in butter, then in sugar mixture.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: pie crust
directions: This makes 4 or 5 crusts and is easy to work with.
Mix all ingredients.
Place and spread crust into pie pans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
The pie crusts can be frozen and used later. Especially good for fruit pies.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk over low heat.
Crush graham crackers until fine; mix with nuts, cherries and raisins.
Pour marshmallow and milk mixture over graham crackers; mix well. Decorate bottom of pan with large nuts and candied fruit.
Pack mixture into pan firmly.
Place in refrigerator several hours before serving.
Keep in refrigerator.
For best results, line pan with wax paper or plastic wrap.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and add dressing.

title: quick pickle relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Add salt and mix well. Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Add sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and vinegar to cover.
Put in jars.
Requires no cooking or sealing.

title: shrimp dumpling with chive (sui gow)
directions: Mix all above ingredients for filling except wrappers.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, oil and vinegar.
Mix.
Add vanilla and water.
Makes small cake.
Double ingredients for larger cake.

title: pear butter
directions: Cut pears in 1/4s;
take
out
seeds and cook for a few minutes.
Mash with
masher,
then put through food mill.
Mix with other ingredients
and
cook
until soft and thick.
Stir carefully.	Pour into 8 pint jars and process 10 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix butter, beaten eggs and cake mix together.
Spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured.
Beat eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy.
Pour over batter.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with a little powdered sugar when done.

title: pecan snow balls
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat first four ingredients until creamy. Add combined flour, oats, pecans and salt; mix well.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until bottoms are light golden brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Pour off fat and stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir now and then.
Serve with hot buttered rice.

title: fruit christmas cookies
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, then remaining ingredients in order.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonful about 2 inches apart on very lightly greased baking sheet (if not Teflon).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grill or pan-fry chicken breasts.
While chicken is cooking, saute onion & peppers until they are tender.
Take cooked chicken breasts and put on platter.
Put onions & peppers over chicken. Cover with cheese.
Put in microwave.
Warm till cheese melts.
Can serve with the sauce.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, butter and sugar. Add the egg and beat.
Add vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Sift the dry ingredients together and add in coconut.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown. Don't overbake.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.

title: jan's chicken
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in crumbs, place on cookie sheet and pour one-half of the butter-shortening mixture over the chicken.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Pour over the remaining mix and bake 15 minutes more.

title: frozen strawberry rice pie
directions: Whip whipped cream (set aside), whip cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Pour in 12-ounce drained frozen strawberries. Combine gelatin and strawberry juice, heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add cooked rice to whipped cream.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: jo's surprise(crock-pot)
directions: Drain first 3 cans. Put in crock-pot. Add rice and packet seasoning. Place chicken on top. Add water and cook all day on low.

title: shredded barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour over meat. Cook in oven at 325° for 4 to 5 hours or in crock-pot. Shred with fork or slice thin. Serve warm.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook and slice potatoes. Add chopped onion and celery to taste.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry but do not drain fat. Add vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil, adding flour to thicken, not thickly, but transparent.
Add potatoes, onion and celery. Serve warm or cold.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: oven scrambled strata
directions: Combine bread, onion, green pepper, ham and cheese.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and bacon grease.
Pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
A family Christmas breakfast tradition!

title: unbaked cookies
directions: In large saucepan, combine first four ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well and drop on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in greased and floured oblong pan and bake at 275°. Cover top of brownies with miniature marshmallows. Return to oven until marshmallows melt.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter and pour into pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in over butter.
Mix cake mix according to directions and spread over mixture in pan.

title: crunchy ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine
macaroni
and
ham
in 3-quart casserole.
Blend soup,
sour
cream
and milk.
Pour half the mixture over the
ham
and macaroni.
Arrange broccoli on top. Pour remaining sauce over
broccoli
and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with French fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: biscuit cups
directions: Press biscuits onto bottom and up sides of lightly greased muffin pan; set aside. In a skillet, brown beef and drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce; cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes. Spoon 2 tablespoons meat mixture into the center of each cup. Bake in 375° oven 15 minutes, until golden brown. Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 3 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: frances wright's strawberry pie
directions: Sprinkle sugar on shell before baking.

title: cajun's all seasons
directions: Mix together and store in a dry jar.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend sugar, shortening, beaten eggs and vanilla together well. Sift the whole wheat flour, white flour, soda and salt together. Add dry ingredients to first mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Pour in 3 loaf pans or 1 regular bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, then it is ready to eat.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Use small to medium size cucumbers; slice thin and slice onions thin.
Cut peppers in small pieces; melt sugar in vinegar by stirring.
Don't heat.
Mix all ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Cucumbers will shrink.
You may put in smaller containers.
Keep refrigerated.
Pickles are delicious.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, water and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add flour and dry ingredients together.
Add pumpkin mixture and flour mixture.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: beef jerky
directions: Remove all fat from meat. Cut into 1/8-inch slices along grain. Combine dry and liquid ingredients to make marinade. Marinate meat overnight in refrigerator.
Drain.
Lay meat strips on dryer rack for 8 to 10 hours at 120° to 135°.

title: vegie dip
directions: Blend together and chill.

title: party rice
directions: Pour all ingredients into Pyrex pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can be doubled.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the popcorn. Mix first 4 ingredients and boil 5 minutes. Add soda and mix fast. Pour over popcorn and mix it to cover all corn. Make sure there are no hard unpopped corn.

title: summertime squash casserole
directions: Wash, cut and boil squash until tender.
In a mixing bowl, combine onion, bell pepper, eggs, soup, bacon, crackers, salt, pepper, garlic powder and cheese.
Drain squash and add to the mixture and stir.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes, until brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all canned ingredients with meat and let heat real good.
Pour Doritos in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour meat and soup mixture over Doritos.
Sprinkle with chopped onion and grated cheese.
Bake, covered, in oven until cheesy, about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Clean fresh spinach as needed.
Chop.
Cook as recommended until tender.
Remove spinach from heat.
Drain thoroughly.
Return to pan and add garlic salt and cream cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and blended with spinach.
Place spinach and cream cheese in buttered 6 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Spread bread crumbs and 6 dollops of butter or oleo on top of spinach.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees. Melt chocolate and butter in a small saucepan over low heat; cool.
Beat eggs in a small bowl with electric mixer; gradually beat in sugar until mixture is fluffy and thick.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.

title: sugar-free date cake squares
directions: Combine dates, prunes, raisins and water in medium saucepan; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until fruit is tender and water is absorbed, about 10 minutes.

title: peroskies
directions: Fry onion in bacon grease.
Mix all ingredients together. Flatten dough and pinch off piece.
Put tater mix in and pinch shut.
Place pinched side down.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Chop spinach in food processor.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with fresh vegetables or bread chunks.
(I use broccoli, celery and carrot sticks and chunks of pumpernickel bread.)

title: 2 chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass pan).
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter (press).
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: egg salad
directions: Chop eggs and mix together with all other ingredients.

title: kraft barbecue oven tender chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until chicken is cooked through.
Prep time:
5 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix all ingredients except corn muffin mix. Then fold in corn muffin mix.
Put in pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Pare apples, slice thinly into large bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg and cloves; gently toss with apples, mixing well.
Pour in pie crust and bake.

title: german cocoa cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy; beat in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add self-rising flour, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Beat until smooth; add hot coffee and stir until blended.
Pour batter into greased and floured cake pans, or one oblong 12 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with Coconut-Pecan Frosting.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Mix mushroom soup, celery soup, Veg-All and broth.
Pour on top of chicken.
Then melt butter; mix with flour and milk.
Pour on top of soup layer.
Salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
It will be bubbly.

title: pineapple poppy seed salad(summertime salad)
directions: Cut the pineapple in half lengthwise through the crown.
Cut fruit away from shells, leaving shells intact.
Cut pineapple into quarters.
Trim off core and cut fruit into chunks.
Combine pineapple with remaining fruits; toss with poppy seed dressing. Marinate at least 15 minutes for the most delicious flavor.

title: peanut butter & jelly cookies
directions: Mix the butter, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla together, blending well. Blend in the flour, baking soda, baking powder, and salt, beating until well mixed. Cover and chill for 1 hour. Heat the oven to 375 degrees. Shape the dough into 1-inch balls and place 3 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets. With your thumb press deeply into the center of each ball. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until set but not hard. Let cool. Spoon small amounts of jam or jelly into each thumbprint.

title: upside-down apple pecan pie
directions: Mix pecans, brown sugar and butter and place in 9-inch pan. Bake at 375°.

title: praline pie
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and pecans together and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 400° oven until pie crust is brown and mixture is bubbly.
Add Cool Whip and butterscotch pie filling to 2 cups sweet milk and mix until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into cool pie crust.
Refrigerate and serve with Cool Whip.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cups blueberries into prepared pie shell; spread evenly and set aside.
Combine 1 cup blueberries, sugar, cornstarch and water in medium saucepan; cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla. Cool.
Pour over blueberries in pie shell.
Chill.
Spoon whipped topping around edge.
Garnish with 1/4 cup blueberries.

title: creamy garlic chicken and linguini
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil. Stir in chicken with red pepper. Cook for 5 minutes. Add peas, cheese, garlic and Cup-a-Soup blended with milk.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes. Toss with cooked linguini.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cut lemon in half and place in cavity of whole chicken. Sprinkle with garlic, lemon pepper and paprika. Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: dilled vegetable salad
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Combine dill, oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables and toss. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Can be prepared the day before, if desired.

title: german beef casserole
directions: Place in greased casserole in order listed except onion rings. Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Top with onion rings the last 10 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and beat.
Reserve 1 tablespoon to toss with blueberries.
In center of mixture, combine eggs, milk and butter.
Stir just until mixed; toss blueberries with flour and barely stir in.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: homemade oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg, vanilla and water.
Then add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until done.

title: chop suey
directions: Put meat and 4 cups water in roasting pan.
Bake for 2 hours, or until tender.
Cook onions, green peppers and celery in 2 cups water until onions are clear.
Drain all broth off meat, reserving 3 cups to make gravy.
Mix cornstarch and cup cold water to make paste; add to hot broth.
Stir until thickened.
Add soy sauce, salt and Kitchen Bouquet.
Cook until thickened.
Layer in pan the drained meat, gravy, vegetable mixture and bean sprouts.
Keep hot in oven until serving time.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Garnish with Chinese noodles.
Serves 10.

title: honey glazed carrots
directions: Steam carrots 10 to 15 minutes. Heat butter and honey.
Add cinnamon and salt. Pour honey and butter over carrots.
Heat for a few more minutes.
Serve.

title: little wieners
directions: Melt all together in crock-pot.
Add cut up hot dogs or small cocktail wieners.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: favorite apple pie
directions: Peel, core and slice the apples.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix sugar mixture with sliced apples.
Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture.
Cover with the second crust.
Pinch edges of crust together.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Cover bottom of greased baking dish with bread crumbs from 2 biscuits.
Add 1 can of tomatoes and juice, 1/2 of the sugar and 1/2 of the butter.
For the second layer, add the remaining tomatoes, sugar, butter, nutmeg and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Stir 3 or more times while baking.

title: puff paste chicken filling(canastas rellenos del pollo)
directions: Use a skillet of 9 1/2-inches.
Saute the onions until they look transparent.
Add the mustarol, the chicken broth and the heavy cream.
Stir up continuously until the ingredients mix well. After these steps, add tomato sauce and the chicken.
Put on the stove about 10 minutes on low heat; stir with a wood spoon little by little.
Finally, add the sweet peas and mix well.
Use this for filling the puff paste, then after this step, bake the puff at 350° in your oven for about 10 minutes.
This recipe can be served with potato salad.

title: bacon-water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon strips in half and wrap around a chestnut, holding in place with a toothpick.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and apples.
Let stand.
Beat eggs slightly and beat in oil and vanilla.
Alternate flour and apple mixture.
Add nuts. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread on plate.
Add scallions, peppers and tomatoes.
Top with taco sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
If you like, nacho chips may also be served.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift 1/3 cup of the flour over the fruit and nuts and let stand while mixing batter. Sift remaining flour and baking powder and add to mixture, using mixer to this point.
Add fruit and nuts which have been floured.
Add flavorings.
Start in cold oven in tube pan, greased and floured, at 300° for 1/2 hour. Reduce temperature to 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Place on rack to cool.

title: creamy sweet potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, mash sweet potatoes.
Add eggs, orange juice, butter, sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and salt; mix well.
Transfer to a greased 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Top with marshmallows.
Return to oven until they just begin to puff and melt, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: good luck jambalaya
directions: Cook salt pork in a large skillet until golden brown.
Add garlic, onion and green pepper; saute until tender.
Add peas, Bloody Mary mix and rice.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat; cover, reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Transfer to serving platter.
(If you can't find peas with jalapeno peppers, just buy 2 cans of black-eyed peas and a jar of sliced jalapeno peppers and season to taste.
Also, I chop the jalapeno peppers up in my mini food processor.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 425° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Can make half of recipe or make and freeze.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: italian chicken
directions: Use 10-inch skillet.
Put in chicken breasts.
Add water, salt and pepper, onion and green pepper.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; bring to hard boil for a few minutes.
Then tilt cover and reduce to slow simmer until sauce is thick and chicken is tender.
Serve over linguine that has been cooked, drained and returned to pot and sprinkled with parsley flakes and olive oil.

title: heavenly ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar; add eggs. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Measure noodles, marshmallows and nuts.
Have ready, then melt morsels.
Then add other ingredients.
Stir until well coated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk and mayo together.
Layer in order:
cooked broccoli, eggs, 1/2 bread crumbs, soup mixture and other half of bread crumbs.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: just soup
directions: Roll hamburger in small balls, or crumble and fry.
Saute onion and garlic with meat, plus bell peppers and celery, if desired.
(I use it all.)
Add potatoes, parsley and tomatoes.
When all is tender, add frozen vegetable mixture and cream of mushroom soup. Cook until tender.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: In large saucepan, brown beef with onions and green peppers; drain. Stir in water, bouillon cube, tomato sauce and paste. Add kidney beans and seasoning. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: boiled custard sauce
directions: Beat the yolks in a bowl.
Add in salt and sugar and stir well with spoon.
Heat the milk to the ??? point.
Remove from the burner and pour milk into bowl with beaten egg yolks, stirring as you pour.
Clean saucepan and pour in the milk and egg mixture. Place over medium burner, stirring constantly, until the custard shows a definite coating of the spoon.

title: best hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If slightly dry, add 2 tablespoons milk, 1 at a time.
Fry in deep fryer at 375° for about 3 to 4 minutes.
To handle soft dough, use wet fingers to form dough and drop in hot oil.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together the night before. Cut broccoli and onions into very small pieces.
Mix together with raisins in large bowl.
Let set for several hours.
Drain, if necessary.
Fry bacon crisp.
Add bacon and sauce to vegetables and toss.
May reserve some bacon bits for garnish.

title: children's bubble solution
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into an unbreakable bottle.
To blow bubbles, experiment using plastic straws, pipe cleaners formed into loops, strawberry baskets from the grocery store, spoons with holes in them and any other items you can think of!
Do not drink.

title: relish(equals 10 pints or 18 jelly jars)
directions: Mix well and add to hot mixture.
Cook until transparent, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Put in hot jars and add lids.
Turn upside down, as you fill them, for 5 minutes.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning mix. Mix bean dips together, chop onions and tomatoes, drain olives and slice.
Spread bean dip on large shallow platter, top with avocado mixture, layer with sour cream/taco mixture, spread with chopped onion, tomatoes and sliced olives and cover with cheese.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with tortilla chips and jalapeno peppers on the side.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix these ingredients really well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot grease.
Turn when brown.
Do not overcook.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: basil-potato soup(6 servings)
directions: Cook onion and mushrooms in oil over medium-high heat until onion is tender and light brown.
Add potatoes and both broths; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, until potatoes are tender.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth. Stir in mayonnaise, cucumbers, scallions, lemon juice, dill and hot pepper sauce. Cover and chill. Serve with fresh vegetables or Melba rounds. Preparation time: 15 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Sift or stir next 8 ingredients; mix into batter.
Stir in nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake for 1 hour, or until tester comes out clean.
If using a 13 x 9-inch pan, you will have enough batter for 1 or 2 loaf pans for bread.

title: polka dot cupcakes
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in bananas.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Fold in chocolate chips.
Fill baking cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: no cook sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers for 5 days in salt water; rinse after 5 days. Slice cucumbers; soak in alum (dissolve alum in water and pour over cucumbers).
Finish covering with water.
Soak in alum water overnight; rinse off and put back in jar.
Pour vinegar over cucumbers; soak 6 hours.
Drain, but don't rinse.
Put a layer of cucumbers and sugar until cucumber and sugar are used up.
Divide pickling spices into 3 or 4 parts; tie the spices in cheesecloth if you don't want the spices loose.
Space it out about equally in pickles and sugar.
Leave for several days before putting in jars. These don't have to be sealed.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend flour and oleo until fine meal.
Pat firmly in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and then let cool.

title: 5-spice casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion and cook.
Stir in seasonings, tomatoes and soup.
Add Minute rice (uncooked).
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunk reserving juice.
In a large (2 quart) microwave-safe bowl, combine pineapple juice, flour, sugar and lemon juice.
Microwave on high for 3 minutes, stirring every minute.
Watch carefully during last minute as this mixture boils over easily.Refrgerate dressing mixture for 30 minutes to 1 hour to chill.
Dressing mixture thicken as it cools.
Combine pineapple chunks and cheese in a medium-size serving bowl.
Pour dressing over pineapple and cheese; add marshmallows and stir until well coated.

title: kentucky butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in well-greased and floured pan for 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven and punch full of holes with fork (do not remove from Bundt pan). Pour hot glaze into holes.
When cool, remove from pan.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for one minute, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well; spoon out on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender, about 30 minutes for whole chicken.
Drain water and cut chicken into chunks.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put chicken into bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Pour soup and milk in and mix thoroughly with chicken.
Melt butter in water and stir in stuffing.
Spoon over top of chicken. Bake for 45 minutes, covering the last 20 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Combine Ricotta cheese, egg and Mozzarella cheese in a bowl.
Spread layer of sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture and put in pan. Cover shells with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: family pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops and place them in shallow baking dish. Top each chop with an onion slice.
Make a sauce of remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover last 20 minutes.

title: orange nog
directions: Mix together; shake or blend.
Chill and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dottie's honey oatmeal bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup real warm water.
Pour boiling water over the oats and let stand a few minutes.
Add butter (it will melt), honey and salt.
When cooled to lukewarm, add the dissolved yeast.
Mix in the flour 2 cups at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Knead on floured board and rise in bowl for 1 to 2 hours until doubled.
Punch down and make 2 loaves.
Bake after it has risen again at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti cheese amandine
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute almonds; add pasta, cottage cheese and seasonings.
Toss until heated through.
Makes 6 servings, approximately 240 calories per serving.

title: seashell macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, tuna, eggs, celery, green onion, relish, mustard, salt and salad dressing; mix lightly.
Press mixture into a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Unmold; serve on a lettuce-covered plate.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg slices, tomato wedges and green onion pieces, if desired.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Mix well and turn into a large casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; top with chow mein noodles and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and cream to fluffy. Add flavorings.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up.
Put in pound pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cold pickles
directions: Wash and pack cukes in jars.
Mix sugar, mustard and salt and add to vinegar.
Pour over pickles and seal at once.
Do not heat.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Partially thaw strawberries.
Mix all together.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be frozen for weeks.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: ginger crinkle cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onion in about 1 cup salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine the soup, sour cream and carrots and fold it into the squash and onion.
In a separate bowl, combine the stuffing mix with the butter.
Spread half the bread mixture in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch pan or glass dish.
Spread the vegetable mixture on top.
Spread the remaining bread on top and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In bottom of round or oblong baking pan, arrange pineapple slices with cherries in the middle of each.
Pour 1 cup brown sugar over the pineapple.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, juice, vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert when cake is done.
Pineapple slices and cherries will be on top to make a pretty topping.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients in quart jar.
Add vinegar; shake well. Fill rest of jar with salad oil.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Layer bananas over crust.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and mix well with mixer.
Pour mixture over bananas. Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate at least an hour or until set.

title: plain muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine milk and egg.
Pour in liquid ingredients; stir only until flour is moistened.
Stir in melted shortening.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well in a mixer.
Have ready the prunes and nuts.
Fold into batter (do not beat).
Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes; in angel food pan 1 hour.
When cake is ready to remove from oven, have sauce ready.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and shortening together.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
Add oatmeal, milk and raisins. Mix well.
Grease cookie sheet very lightly.
Bake at 350°.
Place on cookie sheet by teaspoon drops.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: bean enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray large skillet with Pam.
When hot, saute onion until soft.
Add chicken, beans and chilies. Simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked.
Cool.
Heat tortillas gently.
Spoon some filling along one edge and roll up the tortillas.
Place seam-side down in large baking pan.
In mixing bowl, combine enchilada and tomato sauce; pour over rolled tortillas.
Top with cheese and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with nonfat yogurt and cilantro.
Serves 6.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except confectioners sugar with beater. Heat oil to 370°.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter into a funnel (holding a finger over the hole).
Hold funnel over heated oil, take finger away from hole and let pour spiraling.
Turn over with tongs.
When light brown put on paper toweling and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and grated lemon rind or lemon extract. Gradually stir in Eagle Brand milk. Add egg yolks and stir until well blended.
Pour into chilled crumb crust or cooled pastry shell. Add cream of tartar to egg whites peak. Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff but not dry.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chill fruit; drain, saving 2 cups juice.
Combine juices and pudding in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool.
Fold in chilled fruit.
Serve.
Keeps well for several days.

title: country buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda and baking powder in a mixing bowl. Cut in shortening until fine.
Add buttermilk, stirring quickly, until mixed.
Turn out onto floured board and knead gently several times.
Form into a ball and pat out 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with half the butter.
Fold over, forming 2 layers.
Brush top with remaining butter.
Cut into rolls with floured biscuit cutter. Place 1/2-inch apart in buttered 9-inch pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve with butter.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Place zucchini in saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, tomato sauce and 1 cup water.
Cook, covered, until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix instant pudding with pineapple and juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Spread on bread and broil 4 inches from heat until bubbly.
Garnish with parsley and olives and serve immediately.

title: brandy snaps
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in syrup.
Sift in flour and ginger and mix.
Place a teaspoon at a time on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread mixture out.
Bake at 350° until pale brown (approximately 8 minutes).
When just cool enough to handle, curl around a broom handle and leave until cool and set.
Twenty minutes prior to serving, fill with whipped cream.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add milk and blend.
Spoon in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour batter into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Cool 20 to 25 minutes before removing from pan.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Combine
cornstarch, salt, nutmeg and sugar in saucepan. Stir in	1
cup	water.	Cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir
in
butter,
lemon juice and peel.
Use over gingerbread or spice cake, etc.

title: kenny's famous soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients in a large soup pot.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: ham dip
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cut ham into chunks.
Put ham, pineapple, cream cheese and all other ingredients into food processor.
Blend until smooth or you can't identify any chunks of cream cheese. Adjust seasonings to your taste.
Great on sliced baguette bread.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Saute chicken in oil and seasoning 10 minutes or until done. Layer chicken on shell.
Cover with cheeses, tomato, olives, lettuce, hot peppers and salsa.
Cover with another taco shell. Sprinkle shell with more cheese.
Heat in microwave 1 minute.
Cut into wedges.
Serve on platter with salsa and sour cream to garnish.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 9
X 13-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Over
the juice and rinds of 1 dozen lemons, put sugar. Let stand for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add ginger ale and enough water and ice to make 2 gallons.

title: ham roll
directions: Onto large slices boiled ham, spread mixture of cream cheese with chives and a little onion juice smoothly.
Roll tightly. Refrigerate.
When ready to use, cut crosswise into bite-sized pieces.
Serve on round crackers.

title: ellen's pineapple cake
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients and bake for 20-25 minutes at 350 F in 3 9-inch cake pans.

title: purple cow
directions: Mix with beaters or blender the grape juice and milk.
Blend in the ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper, 1/2 of the tomato sauce, and 1/2 teaspoon of the oregano.
On waxed paper, pat into rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Roll up by starting on short side.
Lift paper until meat begins to roll tightly.
Peel back paper to keep it free. Continue lifting and peeling to complete the roll.
Seal edges and place in a microwaveable loaf dish.
Microwave on high 9 minutes. Rotate dish after 1/2 cooking time.
Reduce power to 50% (medium). Microwave 11-14 minutes or until meat loses pink color, rotating after 1/2 cooking time.
Drain.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In medium skillet melt butter and brown meat coated with 1 tablespoon of flour.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in broth, mushrooms, tomato paste, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes or until tender.
Blend in sour cream, mixed with remaining flour and heat through.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Serve stroganoff over noodles.

title: florence neifert's chocolate drops
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add to creamed mixture the egg and milk.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet; bake at 350° until they spring back when touched lightly.
Time depends on how small you make the cookies.
Ice with white icing if desired when cooled.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple, saving juice.
Mix sugar, eggs, flour, soup mac and juice.
Cook until thick. Add cooled dressing to fruit mix with marshmallows. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix in Cool Whip before serving.

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: To prepare vegetables:
Cut corn from cob; scrape cob to remove pulp.
Peel and seed tomato before chopping.
Peel onion; chop.
Seed green pepper; chop.
In large bowl combine corn, tomato, onion, green pepper, cheese and corn meal.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add milk, salt and pepper to beaten egg; mix well.
Pour vegetable mixture into a buttered, shallow 2-quart baking dish. Pour egg mixture over to top.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour 1/2 vanilla pudding over cake.
Then mix strawberries with glaze and put 1/2 over pudding.
Add 1 container of Cool Whip.
Then repeat layers. Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, oil and beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together three times.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Add nuts, raisins and mashed bananas.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add flour and eggs, beat well. Mix in buttermilk and flavorings. Pour into 2 nine inch pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is browned.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand refrigerated overnight.
Keeps several days in refrigerator.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Combine ingredients except mushrooms. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Chill 24 hours before serving.
Serve at room temperature.

title: deep-fried mushrooms
directions: Trim off just the tips of the mushroom stems.
Rinse mushrooms under cold water and drain.
Roll mushrooms in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Beat together eggs, water and oil.
Dip mushrooms in egg mixture until well coated.
Coat mushrooms on all sides with bread crumbs.
Cook in deep fat fryer until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: melonade
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Place half of watermelon in an electric blender.
Puree until smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl and repeat with remaining watermelon.
Add juices and dissolved sugar mixture; stir well.
Just before serving, stir in 7-Up.
Garnish with lime slices, small whole strawberries or orange slices.
Yields 18 cups.

title: barbecue pork roast
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Remove roast and slice or shred meat.
Put back in crock-pot
with sauce.
Serve on buns.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine tomato paste, tomato sauce, garlic salt and 3 cans water to beef.
Mix well.
Boil lasagne noodles in pot.

title: vanilla frosting
directions: Mix Crisco, salt, vanilla and about 1/3 of the sugar.
Add milk and remaining sugar alternately.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin frosting if needed.

title: scallopine marsala
directions: Pound chicken breast thin; salt and pepper to taste.
Season cutlets with salt and pepper; dredge with flour and shake off excess.
Melt butter in a large skillet over high heat and brown cutlets quickly (not more than 2 or 3 minutes each side) on both sides.
It is not necessary that they be cooked through at this point.
Remove from pan, drain and keep warm in oven preheated to 150° to 200°.

title: apple betty
directions: Mound apples in 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: marshmallows
directions: Soak gelatin in one-half of the water for 5 minutes.
Cook the sugar and the remaining water until it will spin a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Remove from the fire and add the gelatin. When partly cold, add the salt and the flavoring.
Beat with an egg whip, cooling the mixture as rapidly as possible, until it is light and fluffy.
When the mixture is thick, add the cornstarch slowly, working it in thoroughly.
Then pour out on a flat surface that is well dusted with confectioners sugar.
Let stand in a cool place until thoroughly chilled.
Cut in squares by pressing the blade of a knife down through the mass, but do not slide it along when cutting.
Remove the pieces, dust on all sides with powdered sugar and serve.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Gradually mix dry into first part; add mincemeat.
Drop by spoonful onto well-greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix well; form into ball and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: lemon moons
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Add flour and baking powder; beat well.
Drop by teaspoon on oiled baking sheets and sprinkle with grated lemon rind.

title: kidney bean dish
directions: Layer ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients with salt and pepper to taste. Place meat in baking dish and pour marinade over.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight, turning meat once or twice.
Broil to desired degree of doneness.
Carve flank steak by slicing diagonally.

title: polish tater dump
directions: Dump all together in large baking dish (9 x 13-inch) except for cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in a cup of boiling water, then add remaining ingredients.
Place in refrigerator.

title: scalloped eggplant with hot dogs(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 25 minutes.

title: rice krispie crunchies
directions: Place chocolate chips in a large, microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 4 minutes, or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter; mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Place by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line pan with unbaked pastry.
Heat milk.
While milk is heating, break egg yolks into bowl and beat slightly.
Add flour, sugar and salt to egg mixture.
Pour hot milk into egg mixture and stir.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cover with meringue.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Slowly add cranberry juice to sugar.
Stir until dissolved. Add pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni.
Add celery, green pepper, onion and cheese.
Mix well.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and mustard. Pour over macaroni mixture and blend.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together oil, pudding, cake mix and eggs.
Blend in water and seed.
Bake in loaf pans at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaf pans or a Bundt pan.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill; nuts can be added, if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Scramble sausage until slightly brown.
Pour off all grease. Add Bisquick, cheese and water.
Make into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
(Can be frozen and bake as needed.)

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Scald cabbage and separate leaves carefully.
Mix rice, meat, etc.
Place large spoonful of meat mixture on one end of cabbage leaf, centering so that you can fold sides in over meat.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Place in greased baking dish.
Mix soup and water; pour over rolls.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer vegetables in dish.
Spread the mayonnaise over top. Sprinkle the sugar over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon over top.
Let stand at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bake 1/2 hour in 9 1/2 x 13 pan at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add egg, pineapple juice and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Cool and then add Cool Whip.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal.
Mix well.
Cool a little, then shake in grocery bag with powdered sugar until all is coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: marian melcher's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with potato chips.
Place in a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour pans (1 large and 3 small loaf pans) and divide mixture evenly.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Slide out of pans while warm.
This is good plain or with cream cheese. Freezes well.

title: grated cucumber cocktail
directions: Wash and dry unpeeled cucumbers.
Grate them and combine with the remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve in small cocktail glasses with crisp whole wheat or rye crackers.

title: shipwrecked
directions: Put browned hamburger in large casserole.
Put onion and potatoes on top of meat.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan, according to package directions.
Mix together in saucepan the 1 cup sugar, marshmallows and 1 cup milk.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add coconut. Pour this mixture on top of hot cake.
Let cool.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a bowl blend softened cream cheese with all ingredients except crab and the 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Fold in crabmeat. Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with reserved grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with French bread slices or crackers.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Combine fresh
peaches and 3/4 cup sugar.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Melt butter or margarine in a 2 quart baking dish in oven or
microwave.
Sift
together
all-purpose
flour, 1 cup sugar and
baking
powder.	Add
milk
and stir briskly, lumps will remain.
Pour into baking dish of melted butter, top with peaches.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.	May substitute other fruit for the peaches.

title: no fail divinity
directions: Combine water, sugar and salt. Bring to a rolling boil for two minutes or until forms a hard ball in water.

title: grilled lime chicken with black bean sauce
directions: Place chicken in a shallow dish; set aside.
Combine lime juice and next 3 ingredients; divide mixture in half.
Cover one portion and refrigerate; pour remaining portion over chicken, turning to coat.
Cover chicken and refrigerate one hour.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken pieces; combine salad dressing mix, flour, salt, butter and lemon juice.
Coat chicken pieces.
Put into a bowl; cover and refrigerate several hours.
Heat oil in large skillet. Combine pancake mix, paprika, sage and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces into milk, then pancake mixture.
Fry until lightly browned on each side; drain.
Place chicken in shallow pan; spoon remaining milk over the pieces and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake at 400° for 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: party punch
directions: Mix 1 quart of water with sugar.
Bring to boil and add cherry jello.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Chill until serving time. When ready to serve, add ice or ice ring and 2 quarts pale dry ginger ale.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add onion and pepper; cook until tender.
Stir in rice, tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper. Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Top with grated cheese the last 15 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook garlic in oil until soft (low heat).
Do not burn! Add paste and water mixture.
Add seasonings.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: fruit loop cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and stir in all ingredients very quickly. Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: peach muffins
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and almond flavoring.
Add peaches and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour.
Stir mixture quickly but being careful not to overstir.
Pour mixture into 8 greased muffin cups.
Sprinkle nuts over top of muffin batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: grape-nuts southern nut pie
directions: Put Grape-Nuts in water until water is absorbed. Combine sugar, syrup, butter and salt. Bring quickly to a boil over high heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add a small amount of mixture to eggs.
Beat well, then add remaining syrup to eggs. Stir in softened cereal, along with pecans and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until filling is puffed across the top.
Cool before serving.

title: great chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken, celery and onion until chicken is white.
In a small pot, heat soups, cheese and sour cream.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed on package, using broth from chicken. Dice chicken.

title: top of the mountain poke salate greens
directions: Poke will be found during spring time.
Clean and wash your poke well.
Cook until tender; drain well and finish squeezing water out of poke.
Have salt bacon fried crispy brown.
Add poke to bacon grease.
Beat eggs when poke has fried about 10 minutes and add to mixture.
Fry 5 more minutes.
Get ready to enjoy!

title: baked pork chops
directions: Combine dry mustard, brown sugar and ketchup.
Mix into baked beans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pork chops, placing them on top of bean mixture.
Lay onion slices on top of pork chops. Sprinkle lemon pepper over chops.
Put in 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.

title: tuna "night before" casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch casserole.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oatmeal, milk and egg whites.
Let stand at least 1/2 hour or refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Bake on hot, Pammed (lightly oiled) griddle.
Makes 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread as directed on package.
Cool and crumble.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix with Miracle Whip and chill.

title: cherry tarts
directions: You will also need 1 package small baking cups.

title: gold brick fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a heavy pot.
Bring to roaring boil and boil approximately 9 minutes (soft ball stage). Remove from fire. Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered pan. When cool, cut into squares and store in cool place.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thinly.
Slice cheese and onion thinly.
Place in layers in casserole dish (potatoes, cheese and onion) until completed.
Pour can of soup on top.
Rinse can with water and pour over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix and eggs together.
Fold in the pie filling.
Place in the greased pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cake cool thoroughly.

title: carrots with onions(microwave side dish)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine carrots, onion, water, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes (10 to 12 minutes in low wattage ovens) or until carrots are crisp-tender, stirring once.
Add margarine and toss to coat. Yields 4 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Put cornmeal in stew pot with water and seasoning. Cook on low burner. Stir constantly. Don't allow lumps in mush.
Cook about 40 minutes. Cook onion and green pepper in a little hot fat until tender. Add meat and brown lightly.
Add all of the next 8 ingredients. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes until thick; set aside for now.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut for 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in coconut and pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: beef tips and noodles
directions: Cook the beef in a crock-pot slowly for 4 to 5 hours in the mushroom soup and the onion soup mix. Cook the noodles as directed on the package. Pour beef mixture over noodles and serve.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at all joints.
Throw away wing tips.
Place wings on paper towels until all water is absorbed.
Spread wings on sheet pan.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in 2 tablespoons of oleo.
Add soup, milk and water; add rice and broccoli.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; remove and cover with grated cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: squirrel mulligon
directions: Cover squirrel with water; add pepper and onion and boil until tender.
Take meat off bones and add to broth.
Wash rice and add to mixture.
Add other ingredients, reduce heat and simmer until rice is done.

title: lazy day bars
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in bowl; mix well.
Stir in eggs, water and cake mix.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in walnuts and chips.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: italian spinach soup
directions: Cook spinach in 1 cup boiling broth, about 5 minutes; drain. Return liquid to remaining broth. In soup kettle, heat oil. Add spinach, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Cook over low heat 2 minutes. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Beat eggs with cheese. Add spinach; mix well. Slowly pour boiling broth over spinach mixture, stirring constantly. Simmer 2 or 3 minutes. Eggs will curdle and thicken soup. Serve hot.

title: blueberries in snow
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pie filling and pineapple. Let congeal.

title: dressing for slaw
directions: Mix ingredients well; blend with shredded cabbage.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and oil together.
Put the 1 cup hot water in jello and let it cool.
Then pour into batter; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg and cream well.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate.
Blend.
Turn electric mixer to low speed.
Alternately add sifted dry ingredients, milk and cherry juice.
Fold in cherries and nuts. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° about 40 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: friday seashell salad
directions: Combine shell macaroni with onion, French dressing, salt, basil, garlic powder, pepper and lemon juice; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Add shrimp, celery, green pepper and mayonnaise. Toss lightly.
Serve well chilled.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Cook meat, onion, salt and pepper in a skillet until meat is done.
Mix soups, milk, sauce and green chilies in saucepan. Combine all ingredients.
Line bottom of casserole dish with tortilla chips.
Layer meat mixture and grated cheese.
Repeat layers until all meat mixture is used.
End up with layer of chips on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: snappy spinach dip
directions: Combine in mixing bowl, soup mix, sour cream, yogurt, spinach and onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables or crackers.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: pea salad
directions: Dice cheese or use shredded cheese; combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Serves 6.

title: turtle bars
directions: Place cake mix, melted butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a bowl.
Beat at high speed until well mixed.
Place 1/2 the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Press to bottom (with wax paper). Bake in preheated oven, 350°, for 6 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Unwrap caramels and melt with 1/3 cup evaporated milk until smooth. Pour this over the cooled baked mixture. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and chocolate pieces.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the crackers.
Spread into greased casserole dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine and mix with crackers.
Spread over potato mixture.
Bake in 350° oven on bottom rack for 1 hour.

title: yummy pie
directions: Melt margarine; add chips and keep over heat until chips are melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: southern corn bread dressing
directions: Stewart's was a drug store in Waikiki, Hawaii that had a small restaurant. They were famous for their orange bread that they served plain, toasted or in French toast.

title: crunchy coleslaw(12 servings)
directions: In large bowl, combine cabbage, walnuts, raisins and carrots.

title: apple bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add oil and sugar. Add vanilla and dry ingredients. Make a stiff batter and fold in apples. Grease pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Stir in cream cheese and marshmallows.
Cut in pineapple, nuts and Miracle Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: ranch potato skins
directions: Quarter the baked potatoes. Scoop out insides of potatoes and combine with 1/4 cup of sour cream and the Ranch dressing. Fill skins with the mixture and top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: sweet and sour beef and cabbage
directions: Cook ground chuck, onion, celery and green pepper in large skillet over medium heat until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain, pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe skillet and clean.
Return meat mixture to skillet and sprinkle with parsley, salt and garlic powder.
Put cabbage over top.

title: barbara devery's tex mex potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in baking pan with melted butter, onion and garlic.
Cook in 400° oven for 35 minutes.
Then add remaining ingredients and cover with aluminum foil.
Cook 25 minutes longer. Stir and cook 10 minutes longer, uncovered.
Salt and pepper to taste before or after cooking.

title: layered peach delight
directions: Place ingredients in a glass baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked crabmeat
directions: Saute pepper, onion, green onion and celery in small amount of butter.
Combine crabmeat and all ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May be prepared ahead of time.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in pie shell. Cover with other pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat fettucine alfredo(low-fat; includes cottage cheese and milk)
directions: Cook fettucine in boiling water according to package directions.

title: shrimp marinara
directions: In 2 qt. pan cook onion, pepper and garlic in oil. Add chopped tomatoes liquid, tomato paste & seasonings. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Add shrimp & cook 3 minutes longer.

title: hot pepper spread
directions: Wash peppers, cut off ends, grind (seeds and all) in food processor.
Mix ground peppers with quart minus 1 cup vinegar. Add mustard, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring often, cooking 15 minutes.
Mix 1 cup of vinegar, flour, water and cook until it starts to thicken.
Mix with pepper mixture and cook until desired thickness for spreading.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: seafood-potato chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, bring undrained tomatoes and 2 cups water to a boil; add frozen halibut, vegetables and shrimp.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Cover; bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to break up.
Top with cheese.
Serves 8.

title: apple stuffing
directions: Saute onions, celery and apples in butter until tender.
Add salt, sugar and bread crumbs.
Put into casserole pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate. Bake at 400° until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with parsley, if desired. Refrigerate any remaining pie.
Make 6 to 8 servings.

title: buffet sandwich tray
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Add salt and pepper. Spread 1/2-inch thick in center of large platter.
Arrange following ingredients in strips on cream cheese mixture: olives, sieved egg whites topped with sieved egg yolks, ham, tomato, chicken and green onions.
Chill until serving time.
Arrange bread around edge of platter just before serving.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.
May substitute crabmeat and tiny shrimp.

title: italian chicken
directions: Put chicken strips in large Ziploc bag.
Pour in Italian dressing and zip shut.
Marinate for at least 1 hour.
Can be refrigerated and left overnight.
Heat butter in frying pan and add chicken.
Cook until chicken is done.
Serve with linguine, salad and Italian bread.

title: sesame seed bread
directions: Mix 1
recipe
of Bisquick biscuit recipe.
Melt butter in a 9 x	13-inch
baking dish.
Add mix to butter.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Alternate layers of zucchini, onion, tomato and green pepper in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Season.
Cut cheese slices in half diagonally.
Place atop casserole.
Sprinkle with bread cubes drizzled with butter.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until tender.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water following package directions.
Drain.
Combine oregano with spaghetti sauce.
In a greased 10 x 6 x 11 1/2-inch baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, using sauce for top layer.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic lightly with water over medium heat.
Add seasonings.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles until almost done; drain.
Cover bottom of greased baking dish with 1 1/2 cups of beef and tomato mixture.
Place 1/2 of noodles, one at a time, in the dish until beef mixture is covered.
Spread 1/2 of the sour cream or cottage cheese on noodles.
Sprinkle 1/2 of Parmesan cheese and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers once.
Top with remaining beef mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: brie and sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Trim rind from Brie; cut into cubes.
Set aside.
Cook sausage, stirring until crumbled and no longer pink.

Cut crust from bread and place evenly in 13 x 9 lightly greased baking dish. Layer evenly with bread slices, sausage, Brie and grated cheese. Whisk together 5 eggs, 2 cups whipping cream and next four ingredients; pour evenly over cheeses.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Whisk remaining 2 eggs and 1 cup whipping cream; pour over chilled mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.
Servings: 1.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Combine biscuit mix, crumbled sausage, and shredded cheese. Mix well; roll in balls about the size of walnuts.
Flatten with fork or leave in balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet or freeze and bake when needed.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: hawaiian style yams
directions: Slice yams into 1/2-inch thick pieces.
Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in 2-quart casserole. Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and pecans.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
