If dish is not hot and topping is not melted after 2 minutes, rotate 1/4 turn before continuing to microwave.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches on bottom of a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sift together dry ingredients; add egg, tossing with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over peaches. Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Partially cook vegetables according to package instructions. Drain well.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add soup, cheese, mushrooms and 1/2 cup crumbs.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add
milk and can of corn and beat again.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: almonation cake
directions: Grease four 8 or 9-inch cake pans and lightly sprinkle with flour. Set aside.

title: lemon icebox pie(easy to bake dessert)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into crusts.
Chill. Yields 2 pies.

title: spicy shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
In a large skillet, low heat, melt butter and oil, add garlic and shallots, saute 2 minutes without browning.
Add shrimp, increase heat slightly and cook shrimp 3 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Remove to bowl, scraping all sauce.
Add lemon juice and dill.
Toss well, cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix sugar, water, coffee, vinegar, mustard and salt together in saucepan.
Start oven at 350°.
Arrange layers of sliced onion and beans in casserole.
Pour in mixture.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Remove cover; stir in cognac.
Continue baking without a cover for 30 minutes more.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine soups and seasonings in saucepan; gradually add broth and bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Pour in layers:
soup, rice and chicken, ending with soup mixture on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir after 10 minutes of cooking.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble baked and cooled cornbread in large bowl.
Chop green onions (including green part), bell pepper, radishes and tomatoes. Add this to cornbread.
Combine mayonnaise, cucumber dressing and mustard and toss lightly into cornbread mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chewy charlie's chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, mix the sugar, cocoa,
margarine and milk. Bring to a boil and let it boil for 1 minute and 10 seconds. Take it off heat and then add the peanut butter, Minute oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir until it gets thick and starts to lose its shine.
Finally spoon out on wax paper and chill.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook onions, garlic, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in bacon grease 15 minutes.
Add beans.
Break up bacon and put on top of casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Stir several times.

title: ice cream
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt to scalded milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Add small amount of hot milk to beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Then add remaining milk to egg mixture and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it begins to thicken and coat spoon.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Allow to cool.
Add evaporated milk before freezing. Makes 1 gallon.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and red hots in 3 cups boiling water, stirring until they dissolve.
Stir in applesauce, lemon juice and salt.
Chill until set in an 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch pan or mold.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut bread dough into pieces and put into greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bring the sugars, butter and ice cream to a boil and pour over the cut up bread dough. Let rise for 30 or 60 minutes. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix in blender egg, potatoes, pepper, onion, ketchup and dampened bread.
Mix with ground beef and sausage thoroughly. Bake at 350° until done (about 45 minutes or 1 hour).
Cover top lightly with more ketchup and continue to bake about 15 minutes.

title: simple and easy pie crust
directions: Makes 1 (9-inch) single crust.

title: banana split pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Spread pudding over crust.
Layer fruit.
Repeat pudding and fruit.
Top with Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Serve with Hershey's syrup over top.

title: deep-fried turkey
directions: Clean and rinse turkey.
Rub or inject with spices or marinade. Pour oil into pot to line based on weight.
Heat oil to 325°. Insert turkey in pot.
Cook based at 3 1/2 minutes per pound or until timer pops out.
Temperature of meat should be 180° by bone when done.
Remove from pot, let cool and slice.

title: cheesy sausage loaf
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Brown sausage links.
Drain on paper towels.
Halve each lengthwise; set aside.
In saucepan, melt butter. Stir in flour.
Add milk all at once. Cook until thick and bubbly. Add cheese slowly, stirring until melted. Beat eggs with mixer and gradually add to hot cheese mixture.
Stir in macaroni. Arrange sausage links, cut sides toward center, along the two long sides of a loaf pan.
Spoon macaroni and cheese mix into center. Cover loosely with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set. After 10 minutes, invert onto serving platter.
Garnish with pimento strips. Serves 6.

title: homestyle pork n pintos
directions: Wash beans thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot on high 5 to 6 hours, on low 10 to 12 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, rice, onion, soup, salt, pepper, lemon juice and nuts.
Mix mayonnaise and water and mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover mixture with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dagwood's delight
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Place in layers alternating meat and cheese.
Cover with top half of bread.
Wrap in foil; put in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into 4-inch serving sizes.
Serve with mustard, mayonnaise, lettuce, tomatoes, black olives, onions, pickles, etc.
Delicious!

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion until pink is gone.
Add salt and pepper to taste

title: darlene's garlic potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into slices.
Dice onion; slice butter.
Layer butter, potatoes, onion and garlic
to top of bread pan. Bake at 375°
until tender.

title: pineapple wine coolers
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart container, combine first 4 ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill; serve over ice.
Garnish with pineapple and cherries.
Makes about ten 6 ounce servings.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; mix well.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen passion dessert
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze like ice cream.

title: lattice-topped turkey pie
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Spoon into lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: pumpkin streusel squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugars.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserving 1 cup crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom and halfway up sides of 12 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: hawaiian green
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 6 hours. Scoop out the middle of some Hawaiian bread and fill it with the dip mixture or spread it on your favorite cracker.

title: hot tea
directions: Cook or boil first 4 ingredients, for 20 minutes.
Steep, strain.
To this, add sweetener, pineapple juice and enough water to make 1 gallon.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Saute onion, green onions, celery, carrot, green pepper, red pepper and garlic in butter until vegetables are tender and liquid is absorbed.
Cool and reserve.
Combine salt, cayenne, black pepper, white pepper, cumin and nutmeg and add to vegetable mixture.
Stir in half and half, catsup, beef, pork, eggs and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Form into loaf and place on greased baking sheet or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Pour off excess fat.
Slice and serve with gravy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Beat all ingredients except maraschino cherries in large bowl on low speed 15 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Stir in maraschino cherries.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Immediately loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove it onto a wire rack.
Cool completely before slicing.
Can wrap and freeze bread up to 3 months.

title: sugar cured meat
directions: Place hams or shoulders into tub; rub mixture of ingredients into meat for about 5 minutes.
Let lay 2 or 3 days, then wrap meat in paper.
Put in brown paper bag and put in cloth bag with hock end down and hang.
(Be sure the hock end is down when you hang the meat.)
Makes enough for 10 hams.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Add 1 egg, bread, soups, salt and pepper. Stir together and place in greased pan. In skillet melt margarine and crushed saltines. Saute until golden brown. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend together white cake mix and Jell-O.
Add oil and milk. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in half of the coconut, half of the nuts and half of the thawed strawberries and juice.
Pour into 3 greased 8-inch layer pans and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out on cake racks to cool.
Put the layers together and cover outside with frosting.

title: snowballs
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add sugar and stir; add egg and stir.
Add dates and mix thoroughly.
Let cool about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls, then roll in coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix well, then fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in tube pan and bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: cherry punch
directions: Thaw and reconstitute lemonade in large punch bowl according to label directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Makes 16 servings.

title: mushroom pate
directions: In heavy skillet, saute shallot and mushrooms in butter; add pepper, salt and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Cool.
Stir in 1/2 cup toasted walnuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve in crock at room temperature with crackers.
Garnish with parsley and walnuts. Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ben's mom's spanish rice
directions: Pour oil in a large skillet pan over medium heat. Saute garlic, onions and salt until slightly browned.
Add rice; continue to saute until rice is slightly browned.
Remove from heat; add 1 can tomato sauce and water or broth.
If desired, add in optional ingredients at this time. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Lower flame, cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: dutch country soup
directions: In saucepan, brown hot dogs and cook onion with thyme in butter until tender.
Add split pea soup. Gradually stir in water. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat. Stir occasionally.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes. Drain and place in casserole. Pour soup over broccoli and mix gently. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Mix Bisquick and margarine until crumbly and place over cheese. Bake about 20 minutes at 400° or until light brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Place biscuit quarters in Ziploc bag with cinnamon and sugar; shake well.
Place biscuits in Bundt pan.
Melt butter and dissolve brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Set in pan after cooking for 5 to 10 minutes, then pour into plate.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat the eggs and salad oil until light.
Add all the following ingredients.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch or smaller pan.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: corn fritters(serves 2 to 3)
directions: Mix together corn, salt, pepper and flour.
Beat egg whites and add the egg whites last.
Fry quickly in vegetable oil until brown on both sides.
Make like pancakes.
Serve with ham, bacon or sausage.

title: shrimp linguini
directions: Season shrimp with Tony Chacherie.
Melt margarine and butter with olive oil.
Add garlic and saute until light brown for 1 minute.
Add seasonings and mushrooms.
Then add shrimp.
After shrimp have turned pink, add parsley, lemon juice, wine and bread crumbs.
Cook, stirring until shrimp are done, about 6, 8 or 10 minutes, depending on size of shrimp.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place half the beans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread half the soup over the beans.
Arrange a layer of the sliced water chestnuts and half the onions.
Add remaining beans, soup and onions.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: casey's lemon curd
directions: Mix the ingredients in a microwave container.*
Cook for 1 minute on High in the microwave; stir with a whisk.
Continue cooking 1 minute and stirring until the mixture turns a little clear and bubbles evenly.
Pour in jars.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Make cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.

When completely cooled, cut into 1/2-inch squares. Prepare chocolate pudding according to package directions. Crumble half of the cake lightly in the bottom of a large bowl, cake will be in bite size pieces.
Then layer half of the pudding. Next, layer half of Cool Whip.
Then layer half of candy bars. Repeat layers, refrigerate.
Can be made a day ahead of time.

title: rice and broccoli dish
directions: Saute onion in butter. Cook and drain chopped broccoli.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Combine all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish. Grate cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and pepperoni.
Drain well.
Cook noodles in boiling broth or water until tender.
In casserole, put layers of hamburger, noodles and cheese.
Then pour spaghetti sauce over this.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: southwestern chili casserole
directions: In a small bowl, blend 1 cup beef broth, tomato paste, and taco seasoning mix; set aside.
In saucepan, over high heat, combine remaining broth and enough water to equal 1 3/4 cups liquid; heat to a boil.
Add rice and cook according to package directions.
In a large skillet, over medium-high heat, brown beef and onion until done; pour off fat.
In a 2 qt. casserole, layer 1/3 each of rice, corn, meat mixture and reserved sauce; repeat layers twice, combining the last portion of meat and sauce for the last layer. Cover.
Bake at 375 degree for 40 to 45 minutes or until hot. Garnish with corn chips.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: macaroon pie
directions: Mix
and
put in buttered pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Empty Bismix into large bowl; stir in water.
Beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and butter.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with the cheese; dot with butter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: curried fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, salt, curry powder and paprika; mix well and set aside.
Combine the egg and milk in a shallow bowl and beat until blended. Dip chicken in the egg mixture and dredge in the flour mixture.
Fry chicken in hot oil (350°) 10 to 15 minutes on each side; or you may bake this in a deep dish in the oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 10 minute taco salad
directions: In a sauce pan or microwave safe bowl heat the beans.
Place corn chips on a large platter.
Top with beans, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, onions, olives, salsa and sour cream.
Serve immediately. Yield: 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, flour and vanilla together to make dough.
Roll to fit pie pan.
Prick with fork and bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Salt pimento and let stand several hours.
Grind all together. Add Miracle Whip dressing to which has been added about a tablespoon sugar and a teaspoon prepared mustard.
Whip all together real hard.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: Heat soup, water and rice.
Place chicken in bottom of pan. Cover with the soup mixture. Cover pan with foil; do not open oven or pan until baked 2 hours at 350°.

title: apple relish
directions: First, prepare the fruit. Core and grind about 3 pounds fully ripe apples.
Measure 4 cups into a very large saucepan.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a large bowl, cut margarine in chunks.
Add chips.
Melt in microwave.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Melt in microwave again until real creamy.
Add box of Rice Chex; mix well.
Put box of powdered sugar in a brown paper bag.
Pour your Chex mix in powdered sugar.
Shake well until all the Chex are covered.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water. Drain. Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion and salt in a bowl.
In pot, blend soup and milk.
Heat. Add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts. Add noodles mixture.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Brown on both sides in greased skillet.
Cover with onions and peppers.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ryans casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on medium 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add crushed crackers on top.
Bake until crackers are brown on 375° about 15 minutes.

title: dede's salad
directions: In food processor, pulse ingredients separately. Then mix together with spoon.
Leave chunky.
Chill.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of soup with rest of ingredients, except water.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 6 patties.
Place in shallow pan or baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Combine remaining soup and water.
Pour over meat and bake 10 minutes more. Yields 6 servings.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel pears; remove hard core and discard.
Put pears through food grinder, using coarse blade.
Combine fruit, sugar and pineapple; cook until mixture is thick and pears are clear.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 7 pints.

title: chicken breasts with dried beef
directions: Place beef in greased, shallow 9 x 11-inch pan.
Put chicken on top of beef.
Put one-half slice of bacon on each chicken half. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: norwegian meatballs
directions: Grind meat very fine, beat eggs slightly and add with milk and cornstarch to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients; beat thoroughly until very light, then form into small balls. Brown in butter, simmer slowly until done, adding a little water, if necessary.
When done, remove meat balls, add more butter to drippings, add flour and brown, then add enough water to make a medium thick gravy.
Season with salt and pepper and add meat balls.
These meat balls may be prepared several hours before serving, as they are just as delicious when reheated.

title: christmas divinity
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in little pot; bring to bubbling boil. When boiling, put lid on and boil for about 2 minutes.
Ready when forms soft ball in cold water, about 240° to 250° if using a candy thermometer.
While boiling, beat 2 egg whites stiff.
Add heated mixture to egg whites with mixer going.
Blend well.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until glossiness is dull, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on wax paper. Yield: 4
dozen.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix
all ingredients together except 1/4
cup
crackers and melted
butter.
Pour into small casserole.
Pour
melted butter over mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of
cracker crumbs saved from above.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour
or until knife comes out clean.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Pan fry sliced onion in butter or margarine until it begins to brown; remove from heat.
Thinly slice peeled cucumbers; place in large pot.
Cover with cold water.
Add onion, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer until cucumber is soft.
May be thickened with cubed potatoes for longer cooking time or with a white flour roux for immediate serving.
Serve hot or cold.

title: light fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips less than 1/2 inch thick. Cook pasta following directions.
Coat skillet with cooking spray. Heat over medium-high.
Add cauliflower, broccoli, onion and mushrooms.	Saute 8 minutes or until tender.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add milk, salt, thyme, basil and black pepper. Simmer 2 minutes.
Place on large serving dish, cover, and keep warm.
Put chicken in skillet at moderate high and stir until chicken is no longer pink on inside - about 5 minutes.
Drain pasta.
Add chicken to sauce with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.	Ladle over fettuccine and top with remaining cheese.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onions and chili in small amount of butter.
Combine all liquids and add onions and chili.
Break tortillas into pieces, place in casserole in layers with chicken and cheese, ending with cheese.
Pour liquid over all and refrigerate overnight, or several hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy company chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put chicken in large dish, single layered.
Sprinkle with salt and etc.
Mix all and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 3/4 hours. Uncover and cook 15 minutes to brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and pat together on pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; let cool.

title: lemon dream bars
directions: Cream together powdered sugar, butter, salt and 2 cups flour. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix soup, margarine and sugar well; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well, then add flour and spices.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: apple stuffed acorn squash
directions: Wash squash; split in half lengthwise.
Scrape out seeds and pulp.
Sprinkle squash with salt and pepper; dot with butter. Peel and core apples, cut in halves and place a half in hollow of each piece of squash.
Sprinkle with sugar; place in baking pan. Add small amount of water; cover and bake in hot 400° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Brown sausages in frying pan; place 2 on each squash.

title: soup au pistou (pesto soup)
directions: Cook all ingredients together to make soup.
Add 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite size chunks (this takes approximately 2 weeks).
Simmer elephant over low heat for 2 weeks, until brown.
Add gravy, potatoes and carrots.
Continue to simmer 3 more weeks.
Serves 2,200.

title: potato soup
directions: Place butter, onion, celery, salt, pepper, potatoes and water in saucepan.
Cook 40 minutes.
Moisten flour with milk; beat until smooth, then add remaining milk.
Add to soup and boil a few minutes.

title: turtle cake #2
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half the batter into the pan.
Bake until done, about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potato and mash well.
Add other ingredients and mix. Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: grog
directions: Simmer the first 5 ingredients on low; do not let boil.
Add 1 ounce rum to each glass or cup.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Remove from heat and add flour, sugar, salt, soda and vanilla.
Beat in eggs and sour cream.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange nog
directions: Blend milk and juice until smooth.
Add sugar.
Serve cold.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and beat in eggs.
Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture. Stir in oats and vanilla.
Pour in greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut while warm.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook the ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Set aside. Place a thick layer of Mexican chips on the bottom of an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish, then spread the ground beef mixture ove the chips.
Next, sprinkle shredded cheese on the top.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.
Spoon salsa on the top and serve. If you like it hot, add the jalapeno peppers.

title: coconut date balls
directions: In a skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add sugar and dates. Cook for 2 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
When mixture is cool, roll in coconut and powdered sugar while forming mixture into balls.

title: fried squash
directions: Dice fresh squash.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll squash in flour mix until coated.
Drop in hot grease.
Cook until brown and floating.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a tightly covered jar. For each serving, use:
1/4 cup mix and 3/4 cup hot water.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together well.
A tasty dip for any fruit, but especially with tart apples like Granny Smith apples.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Beat all together.
Freeze in quart pail.

title: tea shop salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup hot water; set aside until cool. Drain pineapple and add to jello with rest of ingredients.
Stir well; put into refrigerator for about 1 hour, then stir again well.
Serve when jelled completely.

title: hannah's bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water on package directions; add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Heat milk, sugar and margarine together. Dump yeast into flour.
Add 1 lemon rind, grated, and juice from lemon.
Add a couple shakes of salt.
Knead on floured board. Cover; let rise until doubled.
Divide into 3 parts.
Divide each part into thirds.
Braid together.
Brush with beaten egg. Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and ground nuts on top.
Let rise for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Combine in a crock-pot; mix well and heat thoroughly.
Serve with a white tortilla chip.

title: pumpkin patch dessert
directions: Mix pumpkin, salt and eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk, sugar and spice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Pour melted butter on top, then nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until moist.
Do not beat with a mixer.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and pineapple.
Add the bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire racks and cool completely.
Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: cinnamon pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin and oil.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Combine dry ingredients.
Pour into pumpkin mixture.
Mix until just blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: four minute chocolate filling
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa (dry).
Add milk and stir thoroughly.
Let come to a boil.
Boil hard for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Let cool about 15 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: surprise bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan, sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with chips, coconut and walnuts, evenly on top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Empty can into pan.
Mash potatoes while heating.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add to potatoes.
Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Beat with hand mixer until thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and pour over chicken. Turn crock-pot on low and heat until done.
I put on in the morning and when I get home from work, supper is all ready!!!

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Add cocoa.
Sift flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; beat until well blended. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creamy cranberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese into Cool Whip until smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Chill several hours (overnight even better) before serving.
Additional chopped nuts may be sprinkled over the top.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix, pour over veggies and marinate for 24 hours.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Small pineapple bits are good.

title: baked rice
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add uncooked rice and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour all ingredients into casserole except almonds. Cover; bake 1 hour at 325°.
Stir in almonds when done.
Serves 8.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 23 to 28 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove; cool completely on wire racks.
Spread cream cheese frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: easy sweet potato pie
directions: Mix well all ingredients and bake at 350° until set. Makes 2 pies.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Combine all but oranges and beat by hand.
Add orange and beat with mixer.
Bake in 3 pans for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini casserole(microwave)
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine zucchini and butter.
Cover and cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
Combine eggs and cheese and stir into zucchini.
Cook, covered, on Simmer/Defrost for 10 minutes.
Top with onion rings and cook, uncovered, on Simmer/Defrost for 2 minutes.
If microwave does not have a carousel, rotate after 5 minutes.

title: phipps foolproof white bread
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour and stir well. Add softened yeast and stir well.
Add sufficient flour to make moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on highly floured board or smooth surface; knead until smooth and shiny (about 8 minutes). Shape into ball.
Place in heavily greased bowl.
Turn once to grease upper surface.
Cover with dampened, clean kitchen towel. Let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours). Punch down.
Let rise again until double (about 45 minutes). Divide into 2 parts.
Shape each into smooth ball; let rest 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves.
Place in 2 heavily greased loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Bake in hot 400° oven about 50 minutes.
Yield: 2 large loaves, which keep well.

title: "pig pickin" cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool thoroughly!! Frost layers.

title: aunt alice's buttermilk cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff to fold in last.
Cream Crisco with half the sugar, then add egg yolks.
Add the rest of sugar.
Add milk with soda in it and flour with salt in it.
Add alternately 1/3 of milk and 1/3 flour at a time.
Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten, last.
Bake in ungreased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Bake at 325°.

title: baked eggplant palmisigano
directions: Mix bread crumbs, flour, parsley, garlic powder and 3 tablespoons cheeses together.
Beat eggs and dip eggplant slices, first in eggs, then in breading.

title: easy broccoli casserole
directions: Pierce broccoli package with fork.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes, rotating dish halfway through cooking time.
Rest 5 minutes.
Place drained broccoli in a glass casserole.
Gently stir in soup. Sprinkle chips and cheese on top.
Cook, covered, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove cover and cook an additional 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and set aside the cornmeal, eggs, sweet milk, 1/4 cup bacon drippings, baking soda, salt and cream-style corn.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and water, then add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla.
Roll out in finger shape and put on cookie sheet. Put in refrigerator to chill for 20 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and while still hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: strawberries and bananas
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until clear and thickened, then add food coloring.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: new macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare rigatoni according to package directions.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine hot salad oil with onions and cook until tender, not brown.
Stir in flour, cook 1 minute.
Whisk in milk, salt and pepper until smooth. Over high heat, heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove saucepan, stir constantly.
Stir in half of cheese.
Add sauce to cooked and drained rigatoni.
Add peas and ham.
Spoon into 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 of cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until hot and bubbly and brown.

title: ice box slaw
directions: Mix together the cabbage, onions, bell pepper and sugah. Bile the vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt 'n pore over mixture. Shove in ice box 'n eat whin you iz in a slaw mood.

title: sally's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix dry ingredients together well to ensure even dispersion of baking soda.
Add sugar, margarine and eggs.
Stir.
Slowly mix in bananas.
Pour batter into a standard bread pan lightly coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Layer cucumbers and onions.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Can be frozen.
Must be refrigerated or frozen.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave cheese and salsa in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl until cheese is melted. Stir after 2 1/2 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips or cut up vegetables. Makes 3 cups.

title: breast of chicken magnifique
directions: Brown chicken in butter in large skillet.
Remove; saute mushrooms.
Stir in soup, garlic powder and seasonings.
Add chicken; cover.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes.
Stir now and then. Blend in cream.
Heat slowly.
Garnish with almonds.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta with broccoli
directions: Wash and trim broccoli, separating florets into bite-size pieces.
Cook broccoli, strain and set aside.
Heat oil in large saute pan.
Add garlic, saute in oil for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli and toss.
Add pasta and red pepper flakes.
Heat, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, stirring to distribute well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain and reserve liquid from oysters.
Place in a layer in a large baking dish.
Season and cover with crumbs and half of the soup mixture.
Repeat in layers.
Dot with margarine and bake at 350° until edges of oysters curl and top is brown.

title: mexican biscuit bake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine and coat bottom and sides of pan.
Chop biscuits into fourths into pan.
Pour salsa over biscuits and toss.
Sprinkle rest of ingredients over mixture. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: upside-down pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, spices, milk and eggs.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top; add nuts.
Drizzle butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Beat sweet potatoes (use most of juice to mix potatoes well). Add salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, 1/4 cup of the butter, eggs, vanilla and granulated sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup butter, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Sprinkle on top of sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water. Boil until thickened or for about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Place strawberries in pie shell.
Pour Jell-O mixture over top.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: lemon cream pie with ease
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill about 2 hours before cutting.

title: goof balls
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla in bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler over hot water.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yield:
72 servings.

title: one-dish chicken lo mein
directions: In skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat; brown chicken, about 3 minutes.
Remove to plate.
In same pan, bring broth, the water, ginger, pepper flakes, teriyaki sauce and garlic to boiling; add spaghetti.
Simmer, covered, 8 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in vegetables and chicken.
Bring to boiling; simmer, covered, 4 minutes.
Stir in onions.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together spaghetti, onions, pepper, cucumber, salt and cabbage; set aside.
In small bowl, mix together mayonnaise, milk and sugar.
Pour over previously mixed ingredients.
Mix them well.

title: hot apple slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, celery seed and salt in 2-quart casserole dish.
Toss with cabbage and apple slices.
Dot with melted butter.
Cover with lid. Microwave for 4 to 5 minutes on High, or until heated through.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl combine wet ingredients.
Make a "well" in dry ingredients; pour in wet ingredients and mix to combine.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add milk until looks like cake batter. Grease muffin pan or skillet.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: rice rancheros
directions: Saute onion and butter; add rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer rice, green chilies and cheese.
Reserve 1/3 cup cheese, end with rice layer.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese in, then bake 20 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Drop by balls on cookie sheet; press X on top with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken biscuits
directions: You will also need 1 (9
x 13-inch) cake pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat drained Veg-All, cream of chicken soup, water and chicken in pieces off of bones in a saucepan.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake biscuits as directed, but not too brown.
Pour chicken over biscuits and put in oven for 15 minutes.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: three-fruit ice
directions: Bring half the water to a boil with the sugar and salt. Remove from heat and add rest of water, fruit juices and mashed bananas.
Pour into freezing tray of mechanical refrigerator and freeze.
When mixture is thick and mushy, turn out into a chilled bowl and beat quickly and thoroughly.
Return immediately to chilled freezing tray and into the refrigerator to finish freezing until firm.

title: tuna salad plate
directions: Drain tuna, break into chunks.
Cut tomato into 6 wedges. Combine tuna, apple and onion.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add to tuna mixture.
Toss lightly.
Cover and chill, if desired.
Line salad plate with lettuce.
Spoon tuna mixture in center of plate.
Arrange tomato around tuna mixture. Makes 1 serving.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Chop crabmeat into pieces and place in bowl.
Add chopped onions and chopped celery.
Add enough mayonnaise to make moist. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with crackers/saltines.

title: lazy women pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add milk; mix.
Dot pan with butter (oleo).
Pour batter in 9 x 9-inch pan and top with cooked fruit. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until done.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Red Layers:
Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add frozen berries and lemon juice.
Stir until berries thaw.
Chill until partially set.

title: fluffy fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Mix well with Cool Whip and sour cream. Add jello.
Stir until jello is mixed well.
Chill 1 hour before serving for best results.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread frozen hash browns in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.

title: pizza bowl
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add oregano and garlic. On a greased baking sheet flatten biscuits to circles. Fill with tomato paste and meat. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 425° for 10 minutes. You can substitute ingredients with Prego Spaghetti Sauce.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator before using.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press Pillsbury sugar cookie dough into buttered pizza pan and up sides to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip well with electric mixer.
Spread on cooled crust.
Cut strawberries in half and place on outer edge.
Put sliced banana around strawberries.
Drain cans of pineapple and peaches and alternate them around bananas.
Arrange sliced kiwi in center of pie.
Cook orange juice, water, sugar, salt, lemon juice and cornstarch on stove until thick.
Don't boil.
Let cool.
Pour over pie.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot cake(family favorite)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, carrots and vanilla; beat until combined.
Stir in pineapple, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup nuts.
Store in refrigerator. Works well for this altitude.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash your sweet potatoes thoroughly; allow to cool slightly.
Add butter; whip until it is all creamed into the potatoes.
Add sugar and spices, beating thoroughly.
Add eggs; beat.
Add cream and blend.
Pour into pie crust shells and bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes, until filling is firm.

title: golden puffs
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Mix in bowl the salad oil, milk and egg.
Add dry to wet and beat until smooth. Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil at 375°.
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden on all sides.
Roll warm puff in 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture.

title: dill potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes well and boil until soft; drain well on paper towels. Melt butter in large frying pan (use only real butter). Saut garlic for a couple of minutes, then add potatoes and the rest of the ingredients. Pan-fry the potatoes until they are lightly brown.

title: herbed chicken en casserole
directions: Lightly season chicken with salt and pepper and brown slowly in butter in skillet.
Arrange chicken in baking dish.
For the sauce, add soup to drippings in skillet.
Slowly add Sauterne, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking another 30 or 35 minutes.
Delicious served with long grain and wild rice. This is a great company dish and can be prepared the night before.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges (save juice).
Add enough apricot juice to make 2 cups.
Cook pudding according to directions, using the juice for the liquid instead of milk.
Cool pudding, stirring occasionally while cooling.
Stir in the pineapple, oranges, grapes, bananas and any other desired fruit.

title: tuna salad(tuna salad is a lot like egg salad.)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients together and serve on sandwich bread or on top of a lettuce leaf.
Serves 4.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until just tender.
Combine eggs and cottage cheese.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and arrange half of the potatoes in bottom, then layer half of cottage cheese, sauce, rest of potatoes, cheese and sauce.
Top with Mozzarella and Parmesan and sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: venezuelan scrambled eggs(perico)
directions: In a big skillet, heat the oil and butter.
Fry the onions until well cooked, approximately 5 minutes.
Add the tomato, salt and pepper and fry it all together, 7 to 8 minutes, until it is a little dry.
Then pour the eggs, already beaten, and scramble them with all the ingredients already in the skillet.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin swirl squares
directions: Combine pumpkin, 1 1/2 cups of sugar, oil and 2 eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Combine cream cheese, remaining sugar and 1 egg; mix well.
Spoon pumpkin mixture into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon cream cheese over pumpkin batter.
Cut through batter with knife for marble effect.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: chicken soup without the chicken
directions: In large soup pan, add together chicken broth, carrots, potatoes, onion and celery.
Cook until celery and potatoes are cooked.
Add pastina and cook another 20 minutes.

title: linda's pepper pie
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
In medium saucepan, add burger mixture and peppers.
Heat through 20 minutes on low heat.
Pour into pie crusts.
Add cheese and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until crust is done.
Cheese will be brown.
If you don't want cheese as brown, bake for 20 minutes, then add the cheese and bake until melted or crust is done.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Steam cabbage 20 minutes, drain.
Place 1/2 cabbage in buttered casserole dish 9 x 10-inch.
Add 1/2 can celery soup and 1/2 of cheese.
Add second layer of same.
Place crumbled crackers and onion rings on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until brown.

title: guacamole surprise(no fat)
directions: Stem peas until tender.
Combine with other ingredients in a blender and process until smooth.
Serve chilled.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut dry ingredients into shortening until crumbly.
Add water, egg and vinegar.
Form into a ball; roll out.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 large pie crusts.

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Combine with eggs, flour, soda, salt and buttermilk and set aside.
Pour water over bran buds and let stand 5 minutes.
Add bran flakes and raisins.
Mix with first mixture.
Store in quart jars in refrigerator up to 6 weeks. Bake in greased or lined muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: mexicali dip
directions: In small bowl combine all ingredients; beat until smooth and creamy.
Cover and refrigerate several hours to blend flavors. Serve with tortilla chips or assorted raw vegetable dippers. Makes about 3 cups.

title: chicken cordon bleu roll-ups
directions: In glass baking dish, melt margarine and set aside.
Between 2 pieces of plastic wrap, lightly pound chicken to flatten for even cooking.
Remove wrap.
Place one slice of ham then cheese on each breast.
Start at narrow end and tightly roll up; roll in flour, then in melted margarine, then in stuffing mix to coat.
Place in baking dish, uncovered, in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breaded steaks
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Mix flour and spices.
Heat oil in frying pan to medium-high heat.
Dredge steak in flour.
Cook until done.

title: aunt mattie's refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald 1 cup water; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir and cool to lukewarm.
Use large bowl sprayed with Pam.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup tepid water.
Begin adding flour into cooled water, shortening, sugar and salt mixture.
Add egg and yeast water as flour mixture gets too stiff.
Add flour until mixture begins to leave the bowl.
Place bowl in the refrigerator.
One hour before cooking time, pinch off the amount of rolls you plan to cook; make them out and place them on a baking sheet.
Let rise for 1 hour and bake at 450° until brown.

title: swiss cherry cheese torte
directions: Bake two 8-inch round cake layers according to instructions on the box.
Split
each
layer,
when
cooled, into two thin layers.

title: gene's sizzling salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients up in a bowl and you're ready to go.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese. Blend with Cool Whip. Add Amaretto and chill.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in cake pan cherry filling, pineapple, cake mix, coconut, nuts and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Put dry ingredients in a large bowl; mix lightly with a whisk. In a smaller bowl, mix all wet ingredients.
Whisk together wet with dry.
Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam and lightly flour.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake bread for 45 minutes or until light brown. Take juice of the 2 lemons and put in a small saucepan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
When bread is done, remove from pans.
Poke holes on top of bread and brush lemon sauce on bread.
Wrap bread in foil; it will last several days. Also good heated up.

title: vegetable soup(lonaconing style)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In a large cook pot, add about a quart of water, beef cubes and soup bone, soup beans and lima beans. Cook slowly about 2 hours.
Remove soup bone.
Add barley, tomato sauce and salt.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Add diced carrots and onion (stir often to keep barley from sticking); add potatoes and cabbage.
When these vegetables are done, add the mixed vegetables last and finish cooking about 15 minutes.
Add water if too thick.

title: quick barbecued pork chops
directions: Place pork chops evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Easy and very good.

title: barley casserole
directions: Heat (saute) barley, margarine and onion until golden.
Add last 5 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soprano solo salmon
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in greased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: impossible cheeseburger
directions: Preheat oven to to 450°.
Grease pie plate.
Cook hamburger and onion; drain fat.
Spread on pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs and seasonings.
Pour into plate over hamburger.
Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese and bake another 5 minutes more until cheese is bubbly and melted.

title: pudding popsicles
directions: Mix together instant pudding and milk.
Pour pudding into 3 ounce cups and put a wooden craft stick in the cup.
Tear away cup and enjoy.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown ground beef and bacon together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 4 to 9 hours on low in crock-pot or in oven at low temperature.

title: dairy state fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the cream cheese until fluffy. Set aside. In the top of a double boiler, melt butter. Add almond bark. Heat and stir until melted and smooth. Pour over cream cheese; beat until smooth and glossy, 7 to 10 minutes. Stir in nuts. Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan. Store in refrigerator. Yield: 64 one-inch pieces.

title: microwave mocha tiramisu
directions: In a medium micro-proof bowl, beat egg yolks, sugar, coffee powder and milk with a wire whisk or fork.
Microwave on High (full power) 3 to 4 minutes or just until slightly thickened and sugar dissolves, stirring once during cooking.
Place bowl in ice water 15 minutes to cool.
Meanwhile, line bottom and side of 2 1/2 to 3-quart bowl or souffle dish with ladyfinger halves, split sides up.
Brush with about 2 tablespoons Mocha Sauce.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour in container and follow instructions for your freezer.

title: wake-up smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in the blender and process on high speed until smooth, about 30 - 45 seconds.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Cut V shape in French bread, dig out.
Spread mayonnaise on inside of bread.
Combine and stuff remaining ingredients into bread and wrap in saran wrap.
Refrigerate.
Slice and serve.

title: easy delicious rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs well with fork or whisk.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat well.
Add rice to milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Very slowly pour milk and rice mixture into egg mixture while stirring.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Set bowl into pan of hot water, 2 inches deep.
Bake in 350° oven.
Stir well every 10 minutes for 3 times.
Bake another 10 minutes for a total of 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: burgundy bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
(Or bring beans to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.) Add the next seven ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cortney's apple crisp
directions: Peel apples and place them sliced into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Mix cake mix, sugar and margarine together until crumbly.
Spread on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange 1/2 the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In large mixer bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, water and extract; mix well.
Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Pour 1/2 of the cream mixture over cake slices.
Arrange 1/2 of the peach slices on top.
Repeat layering, ending with peach slices.
Chill 4 hours, or until set.
Cut into squares to serve. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper, onion, garlic powder and celery salt.
Mix well.
Set in refrigerator overnight. Make round balls and roll in chopped nuts.
(Optional:
Roll one large ball in nuts.)

title: upside-down pizza loaf
directions: In non-stick skillet, heat 1/2 tablespoon oil; add turkey and onion.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender and turkey is done.
Add 1 tablespoon flour and stir quickly to combine; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in tomato sauce; add basil, fennel seed and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook while stirring for 1 minute.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with Pam and transfer turkey mixture to pan; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with mayonnaise.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving crumbs for topping.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes.
Mix pudding with rest of ingredients, adding a few crumbs and mix. Pour into crust; top with more crumbs.
Chill.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender.
Debone and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Soak tortillas in reserved chicken broth for 15 minutes.
Layer tortillas in bottom of 3-quart casserole.
Add chicken as second layer.

title: tuna biscuit ring
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of the egg; set aside.
Mix remaining egg, tuna, onion, cheese, parsley, celery salt and pepper.
Prepare biscuit dough.
Roll dough into rectangle, 15 x 10-inch.
Spread with tuna mixture.
Roll up, beginning at wide side.
Place seam side down in ring on greased baking sheet.
Pinch ends together.
With scissors, make cuts 2/3 of the way through ring at 1-inch intervals.
Turn each section on its side.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: marinade for barbecue salmon
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over salmon. Marinate overnight.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Saute ground meat.
Pour half of the batter in iron skillet that has oil in it.
Sprinkle with meat, grated cheese and chopped pepper.
Add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cook pinto beans and you have a great meal.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top. Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: angel food cake strawberry dessert - diabetic
directions: Line bottom of large baking dish with cake pieces.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl for 2 minutes, or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water.
Pour over cake pieces. Top with strawberries, reserving several for garnish, if desired. Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Spread evenly over cake pieces and strawberries.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread whipped topping over pudding.
Refrigerate 4 hours, or until set.
Garnish with reserved strawberries.
Yields 15 servings.

title: fresh apple nut bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans thoroughly stir together flour, baking soda and salt. in a large bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, beat together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth. Fold in apples and pecans. Turn into prepared pans. Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Bake at 350 degrees about 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and gelatine in hot water.
Add cold water and chill.
Add ground cranberries, apples, celery, pineapple, sugar and pecans to jello.
Grease dish or mold with mayonnaise to prevent sticking. Chill. Serves 18 to 20.

title: lima bean salad
directions: Drain beans and mix with olives, ham and onions.
Add mayonnaise and toss.

title: judy's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until creamed well.
Beat in egg, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill dough for 1/2 hour. Roll balls, then press with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.
Brush each cookie with beaten egg mixture before baking to give a nice glaze.

title: lumberjack cookies
directions: Cook slowly over low heat until thick and let cool while making the dough.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead dough.
Roll and cut out.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In microwave, melt butter and marshmallows together (2 to 6 minutes, depending on power level).
Stir often.
Grease an angel food pan or Bundt pan.
Combine butter mixture, popcorn and M&M's. Press into pan.
Let set 1 to 2 hours before unmolding.

title: spaghetti squash bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy and add sugar slowly.
Beat on medium speed while adding oil.
Blend in vanilla and squash.
Mix dry ingredients and add to squash mixture.
You may add nuts or raisins if you wish.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 - 60 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Must prepare ahead.
Early in the day put a large chicken or hen in a stew pot and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat and simmer until meat is falling off bone.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Bone chicken and put back in pot.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole as desired and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Combine sugar, butter and eggs; blend thoroughly.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Mix until dough is smooth.
Drop balls of dough from an ice cream scoop onto a greased cookie sheet, or roll out dough about 1/2-inch thick on a floured cutting board and cut into desired shapes, then place on cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cakes.

title: sausage bean soup
directions: Put undrained beans and tomatoes in food processor.
Process until just chopped, not mashed.
Brown and drain sausage.
Add seasonings, potatoes, onion and water.
Add to tomatoes and beans. Bring to boil and simmer for 2 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix together Bisquick, Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken breasts with mixture and place on Corning Ware dish with 2 tablespoons of oil.
Cover dish and bake on 400° for 45 minutes.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over chicken breasts and sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pop's potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; chill well (they grate better).
Grate potatoes; set aside.
Sprinkle a little salt on.
Blend butter and sour cream and alternate layers of potatoes and soup.
You can add a little onion.
Cover with cornflakes and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed cherry salad
directions: Grate rinds; set aside.
Squeeze juice.
Combine this juice with juice from cherries and pineapple in a saucepan.
Add sugar; bring to a boil.
Add jello and dissolve.
Add other ingredients. Mold and chill.
Serves 12.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake 45 - 60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pecan log
directions: Melt chips and butter in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add salt.
Add sugar alternately with milk, blending well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stew beef
directions: Brown meat; add all ingredients, except carrots and potatoes. Let simmer for 45 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes; cook until done.

title: bug spray(for plants)
directions: Mix all ingredients into water.
Use by pouring on or spraying on infected plants.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Separate each unbaked biscuit into halves.
Put a wiener on each half, then fold.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown in a 375° oven.
May also add shredded Cheddar cheese with wiener, if desired.

title: banana berry cooler
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high for 30 seconds or until smooth.
For an extra refreshing drink, add 1 cup of ice and blend well.
Yields 4 (8 ounce) servings.
Good and tangy!

title: easy zucchini casserole
directions: Grease medium size casserole dish.
Line bottom with zucchini. Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Cover with sliced or chopped onion and top with tomato slices to cover.
Repeat salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Top with slices of American cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and pecans, in buttered, 3-quart, glass mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on Medium for 15 minutes.
Stir and continue cooking on Medium for 13 to 15 minutes or until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture forms soft peaks.
Stir in pecans.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven
to
Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Add
beaten
eggs
and strawberries with liquid.
Stir; add oil, lemon juice and pecans; mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into 2 greased
and
floured
loaf
pans
or
make
1 loaf and muffins. Bake
one
hour,
or
until a straw tester indicates bread is cooked.
If
making muffins, place them in oven with loaf pan during
the
last
to
30 minutes of baking time. Cool on racks, invert loaf and slice when cool.
Wrap tightly to freeze. Good
warm
or
at
room temperature plain or with strawberry butter.

title: brownie bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir granulated sugar into melted chocolate mixture.
Mix in eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour.
Fill greased 1 3/4 x 1-inch miniature muffin cups 2/3 full with batter.
Bake for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cool slightly in muffin pans.
Loosen edges with tip of knife.
Make 1/2-inch indentation in top of each brownie.

title: sauteed scallops
directions: Spray saute pan liberally with cooking spray.
Heat pan over low to medium flame.
Saute onions, garlic and scallops until scallops are brown around edges.
Add wine, salt and pepper. Allow to bubble until almost dry, stirring frequently.
Combine melted butter and lemon juice and toss with scallops.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: christmas pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, egg and sugar.
Add Cool Whip and walnuts.
Fold in cherries, sliced in half.
Use the rest to top off pie.
Use graham cracker pie crust.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cook chorizo; drain.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Cut Velveeta into squares and melt.
Mix all ingredients together and serve warm or cold with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Gradually add sugar to moisten ingredients.
Add oil, zucchini and flour to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Stew chicken and remove from bone.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and milk; heat.
Pour over chicken.
Mix margarine and broth with dressing.
Spoon over top of chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sharp cheese together.
Add other ingredients.
Let chill and form into balls.

title: golden broccoli soup
directions: In 3-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine broccoli, carrot, onion and water.
Cover with lid; microwave on High 5 minutes or until veggies are tender.

title: molasses pudding(it's more of a cake)
directions: To mix, sift flour once and measure.
Add soda, baking powder, spices and salt.
Sift together 3 times.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs, then molasses.
Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth. Bake in greased pan in moderately slow oven at 325° for about 45 minutes, until done.
Cut in squares.
Good with a sauce (caramel or vanilla).

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, relish, dressing, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Add beef and mix well.

title: mama's tea cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients, water and flavoring; knead.
Cool, then roll thin.
Cut and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: rum pudding(romfromage)
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar until lemon colored.
Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup water and melt over hot water.

title: no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: In saucepan, over medium heat, mix cocoa and sugar.
Add margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let harden.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen. Can freeze.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sour cream.
Pour one-half of mixture in an 8-inch square pan; allow to congeal. Spread top with sour cream.
Spread remainder of mixture on top; refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut. Add all ingredients together and let stand overnight.

title: yummy cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar.
Add evaporated milk to the yeast and sugar mixture.
Warm on top of stove or in microwave to approximately 110°.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Sift salt, soda and flour; mix ingredients in order given. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Press flat.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, add all ingredients except cheese and mix together.
In large, greased baking dish, place mixture and top with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 45 to 75 minutes or until rice is done.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Coat onions in batter.
Drop rings in hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: oyster dressing
directions: In a skillet, saute onion, green onions and celery in oil until tender.
Add chopped parsley.
Drain oysters and cut into pieces.
Add oysters to skillet mixture and cook until liquid is absorbed.
Remove any hard crusts from the softened bread and add to oyster mixture, cooking until mixed.
Serves 8.

title: nut horns(kolachy)
directions: Combine margarine,
flour
and	ice
cream
to make the dough. Chill
overnight.	Roll out dough into squares or fill with favorite
filling.	Seal
edges
and form into crescents. Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocado with fork.
Blend in tomato (seeded and finely chopped).
Add green pepper, onion salt, chili powder, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Serve with crisp vegetables or corn chips.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: potato delight
directions: Make the potatoes for 8 according to directions on box of instant potatoes.
Mix in cream cheese and sour cream. Salt and pepper to taste.
Put into pan and dot with butter and paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Melt butter and add to cocoa and sugar. Add other ingredients.
Place on medium heat and stir until it comes to a hard boil (a boil that can't be stirred down). Boil for 1 1/2 minutes. Take off and beat until ready to spread.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear up the bread in a bowl.
Pour enough cold milk over this to cover.
Let it get soggy for a few minutes.
Beat the eggs and sugar.
Add to the bread.
Add the cut up peaches or any other fruit.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Stir all this together and pour in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix the last 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Be sure to mix well.
Add the cut up chicken wings.
Mix well to cover with marinade.
Cover with lid and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
When ready to cook them, line a cookie sheet with foil.
Place chicken wings on sheet and cover with any marinade that is left.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours, turning them if necessary. Remove with tongs and serve as an hors d'oeuvre or with rice as a main course.

title: fire and ice pickles
directions: Combine pickles, sugar, hot sauce and pepper flakes in a large bowl; stir well.
Cover and let stand 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Spoon pickles into pint canning jars.
Add a clove of garlic to each jar.
Cover with metal lids and screw on bands. Store in refrigerator.
Yields 3 pints.

title: turkey or chicken cheese puffs
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Beat with mixer on medium until smooth.
Add milk.
Stir in chicken or turkey and pepper. Separate rolls into 4 squares.
Pat 1/2 cup of meat mixture in center of each square and bring the 4 corners to the center and pinch to seal.
Bake on ungreased sheet for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 4 servings.
Freezes well.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Prepare spinach according to package.
Drain and reserve liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended.
Add liquor slowly.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Combine with spinach.
This may be served with buttered bread crumbs.
Freezes well.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add beef consomme and tomatoes.
Add water, carrots and seasoning (to taste).
Simmer 1 hour.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown hamburger; add salt and pepper in large skillet.
Add vegetable soup and cooked macaroni.
Simmer for 15 minutes; add Cheez Whiz and simmer for 5 minutes or until cheese has melted and blended in.

title: pittsburg potatoes
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour and salt; stir with whisk until bubbly.
Add milk slowly, heat until thick.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Combine all ingredients except fillets.
Dredge fillets in melted butter.
Roll in bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In an oblong pan that has been sprayed with Pam, spread nuts on bottom.
Place coconut on top
of nuts.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together and add powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mix and bake for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and sift.
Add shortening and work to fine crumb stage; then mix egg and cream together.
Pour over the other ingredients and work together.
Pinch off in small size and fill with favorite filling.
Fry.

title: maple glazed apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with bottom crust.
Place half of the apples in the crust; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine sugars, gingersnaps, cinnamon, nuts and butter.
Sprinkle half over apples in crust.
Top with remaining apples and sugar mixture.
Cover with top crust which has a few slits cut in it.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Place in airtight container. Add three to four tablespoons per cup of boiling water.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; cut off tops.
Cook in boiling salted water about 6 minutes and drain.
Cook sausage; pour off drippings.
Add onion, cooking until transparent.
Place mixture in a bowl; add remaining ingredients.
Stir lightly until blended.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Stand peppers up in shallow baking dish; cover bottom of dish with 1/4-inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked beans casserole
directions: Cook in skillet and stir turkey bacon, beef, onions and green pepper until beef is browned.
Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: english apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt butter with marshmallows.
Crush graham crackers.
Mix all ingredients together and pack it in any size pans you want; then refrigerate.
I put mine in 9 x 13-inch pan and cut three. Makes 5 pounds.

title: herb butter for bread sticks
directions: Melt Parkay.
Add spices and stir.
Brush onto bread sticks that are 2 minutes from completed baking time.
Return sticks to oven and bake 4 more minutes.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add egg, shortening and water; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into bowl or pie dish. In center, place the mixture of filling, juice and spices.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crust is done.

title: molasses creams
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses.
Mix well. Blend in dry ingredients.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: watermelon mint salad
directions: Slice the water melon into 1-inch thick rounds.
Cut rinds from flesh and discard.
Cut flesh into 1-inch cubes and remove seeds. Place cubes in large bowl.
Add onions and minced mint.
If made ahead, cover and chill up to 4 hours.
Pour dressing over salad. Mix gently.
Add salt to taste.

title: scratch chocolate cake
directions: Mix
together in a big bowl flour, sugar, cocoa, cinnamon
and salt.
Melt
in
a
saucepan 1 stick butter, oil and water; bring
to a boil.
Add dry with liquid ingredients and mix well. Add beaten eggs, soda and buttermilk.
Add vanilla. Stir
all together and pour into a greased, floured pan.
Cook at
for 30
to
40 minutes.
While cake is hot from the oven, pour frosting on it.

title: peanut butter yo-yos
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugars and egg.
Blend in remaining ingredients except jelly.
Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until set but not hard.
Put cookies together in pairs with jelly in middle.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: elderberry jelly
directions: Mix original juice with 1 cup water to 1/2 gallon of juice. Mix all the ingredients together in a large stockpot until all ingredients are well blended.
Cook over low to medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add hot mixture to well sterilized hot jars (canning).
Seal with sterilized lids.
Cover with small towel or dish cloths.
Let stand until next day.
Jars are sealed when you hear a slight popping sound.

title: tabbuli salad
directions: Combine bulgur wheat with cold water and allow to stand for at least an hour to absorb moisture.
Then combine bulgur wheat with parsley, chopped green pepper, minced onions, mint and tomatoes. Stir together oil and lemon juice; pour over wheat and mix well. Add salt, if desired (1 teaspoon).
Chill if made ahead.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables.
Mix with pimento, onion, pepper and celery. Mix other ingredients together.
Heat until boiling.
Can be microwaved.
Pour over vegetables.	Stir well.
Let set overnight. Keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.
(I usually double this recipe.)

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put into covered pan for 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
Break up meat. Drain.
Save liquid.
Put meat back into liquid.
Serve on hamburger or steak buns.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat together for 5 minutes the first 5 ingredients with an electric mixer.
Pour into jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Break off tough ends of asparagus and boil or steam in the usual manner until bright green but still a bit firm.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Cut in 3/4 inch lengths. In a lightly buttered medium gratin dish, place asparagus with bread crumbs, cheese, seasonings, parsley and olive oil.
Dot with butter.
Bake until the asparagus is heated through, 6-8 minutes. Remove from oven, sprinkle with Mozzarella and place under broiler until cheese just melts.
Do not overcook cheese.
Cheddar is safer.
Good with hot crab meat casserole.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Stir together until well blended.
