Spread evenly in bottom of unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.

title: lemon refrigerator cake
directions: Mix lemon pudding with milk.
Spread over the cream cheese layer.
Cover with the remaining Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: easy-roll sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Add remaining dry ingredients and mix until smooth thick dough forms.
Divide into 4 sections, wrap in plastic wrap and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: 10-minute fudge
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and warm water.
Add vanilla to chocolate; stir.
Pour over confectioners sugar and salt.
Stir melted mixture with sugar until blended.
Mix in nuts, if desired. Press into 8-inch pan; chill.

title: crab quiche
directions: Note:
Cooked sausage or bacon bits may be substituted instead of crab meat.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all of the above by hand.
Shape as you desire or mold it. Serve with crackers, chips, etc.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla and food coloring in a double boiler.
Heat until marshmallows and butter are melted. Stir in cornflakes.
Drop on wax paper.
Shape into wreath 9-inches.
Decorate with red candies.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add food coloring and blend.
Dissolve soda in the buttermilk; add vanilla.
Blend alternately with flour.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into three greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "use your cucumbers" salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and seed, if necessary.
Thinly slice cucumbers and onions.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Add cucumbers and onions; toss well.
Refrigerate, covered, 2 to 3 hours.
Before serving, toss again and remove salad to serving plate, saving marinade for storing leftovers. Keeps several days.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: slice and bake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Wrap in rolls. Refrigerate or freeze. Slice & bake in preheated
375 degrees oven for 7-8 minutes for chewy cookies or 9-10 minutes for crisp cookies. Let stand for 2 minutes, then remove to wire rack.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed; pour over cabbage mixture.
Put in a covered container; will keep without turning dark for days.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour in herb dressing.
Stir and divide into 2 parts.
Take half of dressing and mix with rest of the ingredients.
Butter casserole dish and pour in mixture.
Cover mixture with other half of dressing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 can of shrimp.
Fold in the other can of shrimp.
Best when made day before serving.

title: butter pecan bread
directions: Mix above.
Pour into three loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°
for 34 minutes.

title: crab pasta
directions: Bring butter and milk to simmer.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and a little Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Quickly stir the crab meat to warm it and pour mixture over noodles.
Mix in remaining Parmesan cheese and serve with garlic bread.
Add minced mushrooms or grated zucchini for added flavor and color.
Also great as cold pasta salad.

title: pan baked beans
directions: Chop onion fine.
Put it in skillet.
Cut bacon in small pieces.
Put them on a low fire and cook until bacon is done.
Put pork and beans in and a small amount of water.
When the mixture begins to boil reduce heat and add the brown sugar.
Cook until the mixture darkens and thickens.
Salt to taste.

title: marbleized brownies
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Cream sugar with butter.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Add to previous mixture.

title: mexican jalapeno rice
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and jalapeno pepper in butter.
Add cooked rice.
Stir in green chilies, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into greased
casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Precook broccoli pieces and chicken breasts.
Layer in greased baking dish, broccoli pieces; cut chicken into bite size pieces and placed on top of broccoli.
Mix together soups, mayo and lemon juice.
Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: salt sculpture dough(not to be eaten)
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large flat-bottomed bowl and mix well with spoon.
Next, add water (a little at a time), mixing as you pour to form the dough into a ball.
Additional water may be needed, depending on the humidity.
Take care not to add too much so dough becomes sticky.

title: no cook chocolate fudge
directions: Over low heat, melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Stir and fold until well blended.
Put on buttered plate and press to desired thickness.

title: arnie's blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Makes about two cups. Refrigerate when not using.

title: sausage and rice dressing
directions: Cook
rice
according	to
package
directions.
Saute onions, celery
and
apple in margarine until tender.
Combine all ingredients.
Makes
dressing for a 12 pound turkey or may be baked in
greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and cut in halves.
Put yolk in bowl.
Add mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Fill egg halves with mixture.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar and vinegar in small saucepan; bring to boil.
Stir in vegetable oil, pepper and salt; return to boil.
Remove from heat. Pour over vegetable mixture; cover and chill overnight.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: raspberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and butter; mix well.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes. Mix cream cheese and rest of sugar; cream well.
Fold in whipped topping; spread on cooked crust.
Mix gelatin with water.
Add raspberries; mix well.
Spread on top of whipped topping mixture. Refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add hot water; mix well. Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: seafood spread
directions: Using hands, combine cream cheese, crab and soy sauce, forming mixture into ball.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, mix catsup and horseradish.
Place ball in center of plate and pour sauce over it.
Surround with assorted crackers.

title: beer batter
directions: Place flour in a bowl and stir in beer, salt and oil.
Stir to blend.
There will be a few lumps.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and let stand in a warm place for about 3 hours.
Stir in egg yolk.
When ready to cook, fold in beaten egg white.
Great for deep frying vegetables.

title: stove top apple butter
directions: In a heavy pan bring apples and water to a boil.
Reduce and simmer until apples are tender.
Press apples through a colander. Discard peels.
Return pureed apples to heavy pan.
Stir in other ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently until thick and color is dark brown, about 7 to 8 hours.
Freeze.
Makes about 6 cups.
Delicious with hot homemade bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken about 30 minutes.
Mix soups and broth; mix very well.
Mix stuffing with melted butter.
Layer chicken, soup and stuffing until it's all used up.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ranchos
directions: Slice potatoes into thin slices.
Arrange in a Pyrex baking dish and microwave potatoes until tender.
Remove and sprinkle with bacon bits and cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Remove from oven and put Ranch dressing on top.
(Unbutton your jeans and enjoy it!)

title: vegetable garden dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with vegetable dippers.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: peanut butter cereal treats
directions: *You can use any kind.
I usually use
Rice Krispies and Cheerios.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix by hand.
Do not use mixer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix and cook until mixture thickens.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat in microwave or saucepan to serving temperature, stirring until smooth.
Serve garnished with Parmesan cheese.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown meat & onion in oleo, add vegetables, tomatoes, salt, pepper, and parsley. Add water, bring to a boil, cover and simmer about one hour. (I use some frozen mixed vegetables with this also).

title: quick cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle baking mix, sugar and nuts over pie filling. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 375° about 40 to 45 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: chicken macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cooked pasta with next five ingredients and set aside.
In small bowl, blend mayonnaise, sour cream, milk and seasonings.
Add dressing to chicken mixture and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: vegetable crispers
directions: Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, tarragon, paprika, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Taking several pieces at a time, dip broccoli, cauliflower, zucchini and mushrooms
in melted butter. Place into plastic bag with crumb mixture and shake to coat evenly.
Repeat until all vegetables are coated.
Arrange in single layer in 3-quart oblong glass baking dish.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave at High (10) for 4 to 6 minutes, until tender.
Some vegetables may cook faster than others.
Remove vegetables as they become tender.
Serve warm.

title: fruity cereal bars
directions: Heat syrup and dry Jello over med. heat until dissolved.
Pour over Kix.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Combine vinegar, water and sugar.
Heat to boiling.
Wash peppers.
Remove seeds and ribs.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips.
Place strips in bowl and add enough boiling water to cover peppers. Cover bowl and let stand exactly 5 minutes.
Drain.
Pack peppers into jars.
Place 1 garlic clove and 1/4 teaspoon salt in each jar. Pour hot liquid over peppers and seal.
Makes 8 half pints.

title: chocolate cake
directions: *How to make buttermilk if you don't have any:
Use 1/2 cup sweet milk and 1/2 teaspoon vinegar.

title: pineanna nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round pans.

title: potato salad
directions: In large bowl, mix cooled potatoes with celery, bell pepper, onion, eggs, pickle cubes, and pimentos.
Toss with dressing mixture and chill.

title: rice-a-roni
directions: Brown beef and onion in a large skillet. Drain. Brown rice and spaghetti in butter. Add beef, onion and broth. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice and spaghetti are fully cooked. Season with salt and pepper.

title: paper cup frozen salad
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice, salt, drained pineapple, banana and red coloring to give pink tint.
Fold in nuts and cherries. Spoon into fluted paper muffin cups (large) placed in muffin cup pans. Freeze.
Cover with plastic wrap.
After freezing, remove from pan and store in freezer.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving to loosen paper cups. Peel off paper and serve plain or on lettuce leaf.

title: cherry-pineapple jello(salad or dessert)
directions: Heat 1 1/2 cups (hot) water.
Dissolve jello in hot water (use a large bowl).
Cool slightly.
Add all the crushed pineapple (juice too) and all the cherry pie filling.
Stir together.
Put into bowl or large rind mold.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown bacon slightly, add onion and fry until crisp.
Add sugar and ketchup; simmer 20 minutes.
Put beans in casserole.
Top with sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: knox blocks
directions: Mix up jello and Knox gelatine in bowl prior to adding water. Add water and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill, then cut into blocks or shapes.
Store in closed container.

title: frog's eye salad
directions: Combine the sugar, flour and salt; stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened about 45 minutes. Add lemon juice; cool to room temperature.
Prepare de pepe to package directions; drain in cold water rinse.
Combine egg mixture and acini de pepe; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly. Refrigerate until chilled in airtight container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place vegetables in greased casserole dish.
Combine cheese and soup in a small saucepan.
Cook to mix. Stir into vegetables. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: honey bunch munchies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together oats, coconut, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
In a small saucepan, cook and stir margarine or butter, sugar and honey over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat.
Pour over oat mixture.
Mix well.

title: cold water chocolate cake
directions: Mix together and sift flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa three times.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
In 1 hole, put 1 tablespoon vinegar.
In second hole, put the 6 tablespoons of oil. In third hole, put 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Put cold water over mixture.
Mix. Put in 8 x 8* pan.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: meat pie
directions: Combine the hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Boil for 30 minutes and then drain the mixture.
Fill 1 pie crust with hamburger mixture and put other crust on top, with some steam holes put in the top of crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Serve with brown gravy over pie size slices.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring oil and vinegar to a boil.
Cool and pour over remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss occasionally to mix.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. May vary in different ovens.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix as directed on box; set aside.
In large skillet, mix together butter, sugar and pineapple using only 1/2 of juice for pineapple.
Pour cake batter over mix in skillet.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown beef and onion. Add beef broth. Bake, covered, 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Add wine and continue baking for 2 hours. Add soup the last
hour of baking. Very good served over noodles or rice.

title: haloupki
directions: Shred cabbage to bite size.
Fry bacon crisp, drain and crumble.
Cook noodles.
Drain and rinse.
Clean onion and slice. Put all ingredients into large pot and simmer together until you can't stand it any longer.

title: longjohns
directions: Dissolve above in 1 cup hot water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 2 eggs.
Add 7 to 8 cups flour.
Let rise; knead and rise again.
Roll and cut.
Rise; deep fry.
Frost with maple flavored frosting.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container.
Cover and blend until well combined.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yam spice muffins
directions: Spray muffin pans with vegetable oil.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: cheesy herb bread
directions: Mix butter, salad dressing mix and cheese until well blended. Spread onto cut surface of bread.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese mixture is bubbly.
Cut into slices.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a very large bowl.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil, beat together.
Mix well with large spoon until all ingredients are wet.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Grease muffin tins and fill 2/3 full when ready to bake.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
This dough will keep for 6 weeks in refrigerator. Half recipe is enough for many households.
I bake right away.
Then when cooled, I arrange on meat trays, 6 on one tray.
Wrap with plastic bag and freeze.
Makes 4 dozen.
Can be made in small muffin tins.
Great for luncheons.

title: stove top squash
directions: Clean and cut squash; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cook until tender. Add butter or margarine and cheese. You can add crackers. Add seasoning at the last minute if you choose to.

title: company chicken-rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper chicken which has been laid on rice.
Mix celery soup, mushroom soup and water.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle onion soup on top. Bake covered 2 to 3 hours at 325°.
Delicious!

title: down home pork
directions: Cut boneless pork (either ribs, tenderloin or chops) into cubes.
Cut all excess fat from the meat.
Cook pork cubes in frying pan with water for about 1/2 hour.
Drain all liquid off. Add broth, soy sauce, mustard, cheese and corn bread crumbs into frying pan.
Cook until thickens and pork cubes are coated.
Pork can be eaten by itself, with rice or noodles.

title: ice water cake
directions: Line pan with wax paper.
Cream sugar, butter, hot water and vanilla.
Sift baking powder, cake flour and salt.
Add alternately with water.
Fold in egg whites.

title: sugar-free lite banana pie
directions: Use blender or wire whisk.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
Cut bananas in bottom of graham cracker crust.
Use half of Cool Whip.
Mix and pour in crust.

title: chicken in sherry
directions: Soak cut up chicken in sauce made with ingredients.
Soak about 3 hours or overnight, turning chicken a few times.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper or paprika.
Bake in sauce at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Arrange as follows:
broccoli, chicken, soup mixture, bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together the sugar and vegetable oil. Beat in eggs. Add salt, baking soda, baking powder, and flour. Add vanilla and beat well. Add walnuts, raisins, coconut, and apples. Mix well.

title: pecan pies
directions: Melt sugars, margarine and Karo syrup together.
Pour into well-beaten eggs, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Chop veggies (carrots, peppers, onions, celery, zucchini, etc.).
Set aside.
Spread crescent rolls on a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° (until brown).
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and garlic powder.
Spread on cooled crescent rolls.
Mix chopped veggies and lay on top with Cheddar cheese and olives.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Break up peas in well buttered pan.
Saute onions in margarine.
Add sliced mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Pour mixture over peas.
In large skillet, mix diluted mushroom soup.
Pour over pea mixture.
Put Chinese noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into 9-inch pie tin.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until crust is brown.
Each serving: 1 bread, 5 protein, 1/2 vegetable.

title: low-fat egg casserole
directions: In skillet, fry sausage, then drain, running hot water over sausage; let cool.
Butter bread (one side only) using Butter Buds.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Alternate layers of bread pieces and cheese.
Beat egg whites or Egg Beaters with salt and milk.
Pour over mixture and let cool in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Line ungreased pan with rolls.
Brown sausage and drain. Sprinkle over crust.
Sprinkle thawed or fresh hash browns.
Add grated cheese.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over pizza.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese on top.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let stand overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Add chow mein noodles before serving.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Place pretzels in food storage bag and crush with a rolling pin.
Mix crushed pretzels with margarine and press into a 9x13 baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa together.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring with wire whip to prevent sticking.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown in hot oven until golden brown.

title: "dill dip"
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Chill.
For raw vegetables and chips.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds.
Place in casserole with almonds on top.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes or until hot.
Serve with Triscuits or party rye.
Even good when cold.

title: good pie crust
directions: Mix together ingredients good and use milk to form the dough. Bake at 375°.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, except soda, together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Reserve scant cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs add egg, sour milk* and soda.
Beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs evenly over top.
Bake for 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook either in boiling water or bake in oven until tender (or use canned yams).
Cool and peel.
Mash potatoes in large bowl.
Add butter, orange juice, brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix.
Gently fold in sour cream and whipped topping until light and fluffy.

title: italian style pork roast
directions: Put pork roast in crock-pot.
Add all ingredients and cook all day.
Try this with chicken.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let sit in refrigerator for 4 hours.

title: skillet sticky chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook chicken pieces until browned on all sides.
Pour off fat.

title: copper pennies
directions: Drain cooked carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight or longer.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: creamed peas
directions: Cook peas; drain.
Add lettuce.
Return to heat; cook just until lettuce is wilted.
Add sour cream and green onion.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: mary ann's sun valley spuds
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch sticks.
Spoon mayonnaise into large plastic food bag.
Add potatoes.
Shake to coat well. Arrange in a single layer on jelly roll pan, so that potatoes do not touch.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn once.
Bake until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable dressing
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add all ingredients except butter and 1/4 of dressing.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Mix butter and remaining dressing.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: wonder pie
directions: Mix and
press	into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: monkey cake
directions: In a
plastic bag, mix sugar and cinnamon; shake it up. Cut each
biscuit
into
quarters.
Put
one
can at a time of quartered biscuits in sugar and cinnamon bag.
Shake well.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter (oleo) and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serve with ham, pork, chicken or turkey.
Serves 8.

title: pink colada
directions: Mix limeade concentrate, coconut cream and grenadine syrup. Add sparkling water.
Serve over ice and garnish with lime slices and maraschino
cherries if desired.
Yields 24 servings (about 1/2 cup each).
Has 120 calories per serving.

title: apple and walnut salad
directions: Toss apples and lemon juice together.
Stir in sugar and 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise.
Mix until apples are well coated.
Add remaining mayonnaise, celery and walnuts, tossing well.
Serve immediately.

title: old-time popcorn balls
directions: Butter sides of saucepan.
In pan, combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Cook to hard ball stage (250° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour slowly over popped corn.
Butter hands lightly and shape into balls.

title: cowboy baked beans
directions: Brown beef, onions and pepper in a 10 inch skillet. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix together dry cake mix and jello.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix first two ingredients in bag.
Melt second two ingredients in pan and keep warm.
Grease Bundt pan.
Cut rolls into quarters and shake in bag of cinnamon and sugar.
Put half of rolls in bottom of Bundt pan after rolled in cinnamon and sugar mix.
Pour half of heated mixture over pieces in Bundt pan.
Place last half of quartered rolls in Bundt pan.
Pour the rest of warm mixture on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes; turn upside down on plate.
Peel off pieces and eat.

title: quick dessert
directions: In your dessert dish, mix together milk, sugar and vanilla. Add crackers.
Top with strawberries cooked with sugar to your taste and thickened with clear gel.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper in a large skillet until meat is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and chili powder.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Make cornmeal topper.
Stir cornmeal and 1/2 teaspoon salt into cold water.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add butter; mix well.
Spoon over hot meat mixture.
Bake casserole in moderate oven (375°) about 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: super special vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except onion rings, in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.
Add onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix together. Pour in 2 uncooked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Form layers in salad bowl of first six ingredients.
Mix sour cream, sugar and mayonnaise.
Cover salad.
Seal bowl and refrigerate.
Toss before serving.

title: fish loaf
directions: Mix lemon juice and fish.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° until brown (about 30 minutes).

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Simmer tomatoes, salt and pepper.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Grind or crush vanilla wafers.
Cut candied pineapple into pieces; leave other fruit and nuts whole.
Mix all ingredients except milk and marshmallows.
Melt marshmallows in milk and mix with other ingredients.
When well mixed, pack in buttered angel food cake pan or into small loaf pans.
When cool, remove from pan and wrap in waxed paper.
Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: white chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter an 8-inch square pan. Line the bottom with foil or parchment.
Butter the foil.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat. Add half of the white chocolate.
Do not stir.
Using an electric mixer, beat eggs with the salt until frothy.
Gradually add the sugar and beat to a pale yellow and a slowly dissolving ribbon forms from the beater.
Add butter and white chocolate mixture, vanilla and salt; then flour and mix just until combined.
Stir in remaining white chocolate and semi-sweet chocolate.
Spoon into pan.
Bake until center is set and wooden pick comes out clean. (May cover with foil to prevent browning too quickly.) Approximately 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Can sprinkle with nuts before baking.

title: cheesy corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 1 hour or until set in center.
(Evaporated skim milk works well, too.)

title: candied yams
directions: Heat butter in 4-quart saucepan over high heat; when about half melted, add remaining ingredients.
Stir, cover and cook over high heat until mixture comes to a strong boil, about 10 minutes. Stir, reduce heat and simmer covered for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and continue cooking until potatoes are very tender, about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat, discard cinnamon.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: blueberry delight cheesecake
directions: Mix the sugar, Pet milk and cream cheese together with electric mixer.
Add only enough Pet milk to mix together.
Layer pan with cut up cake.
Pour mixture on top; layer with bananas. Sprinkle nuts.
Add layer of blueberry filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill at least 2 hours (better if chilled overnight).

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips and quickly brown meat in hot oil.
Add salt, green pepper, onion, soy sauce, sherry, garlic powder and ginger.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir until dissolved and add to meat mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly over low heat until lightly thickened.
Add tomato and simmer about 10 minutes.
(Additional water may be added, if needed.)
Serve over rice.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter, butterscotch and chocolate morsels in heavy saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in peanuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: monkey bread
directions: Generously grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Place half the biscuits into the pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Melt the butter.
Sprinkle half the sugar mixture over biscuits.
Pour half the butter over this.
Add half the pecans. Add the rest of the biscuits and repeat using all the sugar mixture and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Turn onto a plate.

title: vichyssoise
directions: *Mix 1/3 cup sour cream with 2/3 cup unpasteurized heavy cream, shake well and let stand at room temperature for 8 hours.

title: golden carrots supreme
directions: Add butter to boiling chicken broth. Stir in salt, pepper, sugar and carrots. Simmer, covered, until al dente, about 10 minutes. Stir in lemon juice and parsley. Serve.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Mix together cornbread mix, corn and eggs.
Pour 1/2 cornbread mixture in 9X13 greased baking dish.
Add browned meat.
Add chilies on top of meat.
Sprinkle grated cheddar cheese on meat and chilies.
Lay cheese slices on top of grated cheese.
Top with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown (about 30-40 minutes).

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Fry sausage and onion in skillet until done; drain.
Melt stick of margarine in sausage.
Add all ingredients in large mixing bowl; stir well. Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: last minute cake
directions: Empty peaches in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Do not stir.
Melt butter and spread over dry cake mix. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked eggs for brunch
directions: Beat milk, eggs and sugar. Add cheese and margarine.
Mix well. Add flour and baking powder. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in a large cast-iron skillet 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice and add raw beef, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Core cabbage head and place in boiling water.
As leaves separate, take them from water.
Spread out and fill with rice mixture. Roll up and place in baking dish.
Mix tomato juice and sauce over cabbage rolls.
Bake until beef is done, 1 to 2 hours, at 350°.

title: old fashioned cloverleaf rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar to yeast and water.
Scald milk; while cooling, add shortening.
Add flour to milk.
Stir, then add flour as needed to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board and knead about 10 minutes.
Cover and let rise. Punch down and let rise again.
Form into cloverleaf rolls in muffin tin.
Let rise until almost double.
Bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: poor man's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil the macaroni and onion.
Drain. Add the tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Let set for 5 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot on crackers or bread.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Spread 4 cups sliced potatoes in bottom of greased 12-inch by 7-inch by 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour half of mixture over potatoes.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sour cream latkes
directions: Whip for mixing, no spoon. Put 2 tablespoons of batter per cake. Bake on hot griddle.
Very light, much like sour dough pancakes.
This came from Canada.

title: veggie dip recipe
directions: Blend vinegar, oil, dill weed,
Accent,
garlic powder, salt and pepper in blender.
Add to veggies and marinate for 24 hours.

title: cheese spread
directions: Cream all ingredients.
Quick and easy.
Perfect for spreads with crackers.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Turn into a one quart casserole dish. Combine the 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and remaining butter. Sprinkle over mixture. Bake uncovered in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs well.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Add flour, vanilla, baking soda and cinnamon.
Bake about 1 hour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and salt until it forms a soft ball.
Add peanut butter and pour into a buttered dish.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: funny cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and add remaining ingredients.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix sugar, nuts, coconut, butter and milk.
Put in a bowl and cover; let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine dressing, seasonings, pepper, cucumbers, onion and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: hot cheese and crabmeat dip
directions: Blend ingredients well.
Spoon into shallow casserole. Sprinkle with a little paprika or 1/3 cup toasted sliced almonds. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Brown hamburger, then mix all ingredients together.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, scatter noodles on top and continue to bake, uncovered.
Serves 10.

title: stuffed seashells
directions: Cook shells.
Stuff with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with slices of Mozzarella cheese.
Add Parmesan and V-8 juice.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl except the chocolate.
Melt chocolate and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate and cut into bars.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Preferably use an iron skillet.
Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook until peanuts are completed sugared.
(Coated and no syrup.)
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet, separate peanuts with a fork.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes, stirring at 10 minute intervals.

title: pickled crab apples
directions: Choose round crab apples uniform in size; do not pare them. Make a syrup with the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add crab apples and heat gently, being careful not to burst the fruit.
Let stand in syrup overnight.
Pack cold into clean jars.
Fill to 1/2-inch of top with syrup.
Put on top and screw on tightly.
Process in water bath at simmering temperature (180°) for 20 minutes.

title: no peek stew
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot on low heat.
Cook all day while you're sightseeing.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry. Take out stems.
Combine lemon juice, cream cheese, ham and seasonings. Stuff into mushrooms. Top with a slice of olive.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: french bread dip
directions: Drain frozen spinach.
Mix all ingredients (except bread) together.
Refrigerate.
Scoop out bread to make a canoe.
Place bread on plate and make cubes out of leftover bread.
Put dip into bread "boat."
Serve cubes around outside to dip with.

title: cranberry stuffing
directions: Coarsely chop cranberries and mix with the sugar.
Toss butter with bread cubes in large bowl.
Add cranberry mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly to blend.
Makes stuffing for 14 to 16 pound turkey.

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in glass bowl in microwave on low heat, stirring frequently until melted.
Mix in peanuts and noodles. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Let them set until firm. Then serve or store in container with tight lid, in single layers separated with wax paper.
Will keep two weeks if they last that long!!

title: mississippi sweet potato cake
directions: Grease and flour three 8-inch round cake pans.
Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer french fries
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into French fry strips.
Scald in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain and dry well with absorbent paper towels.
Fry in oil until light brown.
Drain and cool quickly.
Freeze separately on a baking sheet.
Then package and store in freezer.

title: hot chicken salad ii
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Put in greased rectangular baking dish. Top with potato chips, grated cheese and almonds. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and oleo and bring to boil.
Then cool slightly.
Add peanut butter, minute oats, vanilla and coconut. Drop new mixture on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add vanilla and lemon or almond flavoring.
Then add flour alternately with milk.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Put in cold oven and turn heat to 325°.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: spicy chicken with yogurt(170 calories per serving)
directions: About 5 hours before serving or day ahead, in medium bowl, mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Cut skin from chicken breasts, legs and thighs.
Place chicken in yogurt mixture, turning to coat well.
(Use skin, wings, back, neck and giblets for stock another day.)
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.

title: cheese ball
directions: Take the cheeses from the refrigerator and let soften.
In a large mixing bowl, blend cheeses with 1/2 cup of pecans, 1/4 cup parsley and the remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer to mix well.
Form into a ball.
Sprinkle remaining pecans, parsley and a generous coating of chili powder onto wax paper and roll cheese ball in mixture until well coated.
Chill
until well set.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes prior to serving.
Serve with your choice of snack crackers.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in 1/8-inch strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef strips, then toss; set aside.
Heat oil in large frypan or wok.
Add beef; fry until brown.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water; add to pan.
Stir until thickened and add tomatoes; heat through.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Mix first three ingredients together and place in buttered quiche dish or pan.
In blender or with a whisk, mix next four ingredients and pour over ingredients in dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
May substitute Egg Beaters for eggs and use skim milk to lower fat content.
Serves four.

title: molasses stack cake by aunt bess
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour, spices, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Divide batter into 5 parts; put into well-greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
Spread each layer, except top, with apple mixture or applesauce.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given, mixing well.
Pour into 2 standard size loaf pans or 8 mini loaf pans.
Bake at 350° in standard size loaf pans for 1 hour/mini loaf pan 45 minutes or until done (should be golden brown).

title: white wedding cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy; set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; set aside.
While mixing at low speed, add flour mixture to butter mixture.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Beating well, add vanilla and egg whites into batter; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: snap beans
directions: Place bone or ham slices in pot.
Add water to cover beans. Bring to a boil.
String beans and add to pot.
Add sugar and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 1 hour.

title: debbie's pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together pumpkin, milk, vanilla, white sugar, eggs, evaporated milk and pumpkin pie spice well in a large mixing bowl. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Now combine white cake mix and butter or margarine.
(Debbie and I mix it together with a mixer on low; it will be crumbly.)
Sprinkle over the pumpkin mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Best when served warm topped with whipped cream.

title: texas chili
directions: In a large heavy pan, heat oil and brown beef cubes on all sides.

Add onion, bell pepper and garlic. Fry them with the beef for about 5 minutes. Add all the remaining ingredients except beans and simmer the chili for 1 1/2 hours or until the meat is tender. Add beans and simmer 30 minutes longer.

title: lo-cal pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
In separate bowl combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick spray.
Fill evenly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12/2 servings with 1 bread, 1 meat, 1 fruit, 1 milk and 3/4 vegetable exchange with 6 muffins per serving.

title: marian's fudge
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Put the remaining ingredients in a pan; cook over medium heat.
Bring to boil and boil steadily for 6 minutes, stirring all the time.
Pour pan mixture into bowl mixture and beat; pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in a heavy pan.
Add rice and next 7 ingredients. Cook; stir often, until rice is brown.
Stir in water and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: cheddar broccoli bake
directions: In 2-quart casserole, mix soup, milk, pepper and broccoli. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Stir. Sprinkle onions over broccoli mixture. Bake 5 more minutes or until onions are golden.

title: cherry delight
directions: Line pan with crackers, then add pudding (follow directions on box to make).
Cool Whip and cherry pie filling are added last. Chill 3 hours.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and form into meat balls.
Brown in 3 tablespoons oil.
Add water and tomato sauce.
Cook over low heat for 40 to 50 minutes.
May also be cooked in a crock-pot.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and cool.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 10-inch baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Serve with Bugles.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Almost fill a 2-quart casserole with cut up squash.
Sprinkle spaghetti mix on top.
Cover with tomato slices; sprinkle with sugar.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until squash is tender.
Cover with American cheese; let melt.
If too juicy, crumble crackers on top to take up juice.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together 1 cup flour, butter and powdered sugar. Pat into 7 x 11 pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Steam in colander 10 minutes.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and eggs.
Add broccoli.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Better if made a day ahead but baked just before serving.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook tomato sauce and spices on low for 20 minutes.
Brown meat with onion and bell pepper; drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all together, along with mushrooms and pepperoni.
Put in baking dish and top with 8 ounces shredded Mozzarella cheese and 8 ounces shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: b-danity dessert
directions: Mix together flour, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and oleo; bake for 15 minutes at 350° in 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over potatoes and spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: lone star caviar
directions: In enough water to cover, soak black-eyed peas for 6 hours or overnight.
Drain well.
Transfer peas to saucepan; add enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and allow to boil until tender, about 45 minutes.
Do not overcook. Drain well and transfer to a large bowl.
Blend in dressing and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Makes 7 1/2 cups.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Put flour into slightly beaten egg yellows. Add just enough warm water to make soupy.
Will be slightly lumpy. Place over open flame.
Add sugar and milk.
When thick and separated from pan, turn off heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with beaten egg whites. Sprinkle with coconut.
Brown and enjoy.

title: tender chops
directions: Your favorite recipe for baked beans.

title: party mix
directions: Combine the first six ingredients in large pan suitable for oven.
Combine
remaining ingredients over low heat until margarine
is
melted.
Pour
over	first
mixture and stir to cool.
Bake
at 200° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Stir every 30 minutes.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Slice cheese into squares.
Melt cheese in large saucepan with mayonnaise.
When completely melted, add potatoes and mix until blended.
Layer mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and dice.
Peel green stems and dice.
Mix broccoli, olives, olive juice, eggs and mayonnaise.
Toss lightly. Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lime delight molded salad
directions: Heat pineapple and water; add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Turn whipped topping into bowl; add dry gelatin.
Mix until well blended.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Stir until blended.
Chill for 30 minutes before serving.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour batter into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut while still warm.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until golden.
Add meat and garlic. Brown lightly.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, uncovered, 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until thick.
Remove bay leaf. Serves 6.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over the apples.

title: crockpot wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except wieners. Drain pineapple, using 1/2 juice with above ingredients. Boil 5 minutes. Add wieners and simmer.

title: easy corned beef hash
directions: Add corned beef and onion soup mix to potatoes and mix gently. Melt the margarine in a large skillet.
Add potato mixture and fry until lightly browned.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, alternating with milk.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten until stiff.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.

title: wassail
directions: Combine cider, cloves, allspice, cinnamon sticks and sugar and simmer.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Strain out spices.
Chill.
Heat to serve.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar together.
Cut in the shortening and mix until it resembles a coarse meal.
Then add the mixture of eggs, milk and vanilla.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before rolling out on floured surface to cut into shapes. Bake at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, water, oil and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Place ice cream cones in muffin cups; fill with batter to within 1 inch of top of cones.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool completely.
Spread frosting on tops of cupcakes. Decorate as desired with assorted candies.
Makes 36 cupcakes.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill dough.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken layers
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to package directions. In a well-greased large baking dish, cover bottom with green beans.
Layer stuffing mix over beans.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Mix together soup, Miracle Whip and shredded cheese and pour over top of chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix eggs, soup, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Mix oleo and stuffing mix and add to top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Cover surface of pudding with waxed paper to prevent skin from forming. Cool to room temperature; stir in flavoring.
Split ladyfingers lengthwise and arrange in a 2-quart trifle bowl or glass bowl, using as many as needed to line bowl.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine.
Thaw broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, butter, both sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients together; add to the first mixture.
Drop by teaspoons onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in pineapple.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Lay 1 package of crescent rolls on bottom of cake pan. Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, egg yolk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on top of dough.
Top with other package of dough.
Beat egg white until fluffy.
Pour over top of dough and sprinkle with 1/4 cup of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon-pineapple cake
directions: Mix well and cook in 3 cake pans or sheet cake pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in pan and saute onion until soft but not brown. Add flour and salt and make into paste.
Add enough chicken stock and stir constantly until thickened. Add chicken and vegetables. Season to taste.
Heat through. Pour into pie shell, cover with top crust, cut slits.
Bake at 450° F. about 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: turkey salad
directions: In large bowl stir together soup and mayonnaise until smooth. Fold in turkey, celery, red pepper, onions, parsley and pepper. Serve mixture on leaf lettuce.
Cover and refrigerate any remaining salad mixture.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.
(For a no-fuss, keep cool meal, add a cluster of red grapes and sesame crackers.)

title: cheese yummies
directions: Grate cheese and mix together with butter.
Add flour until well mixed.
Gently mix in rice crispies, then roll into walnut size balls.
Place on cookie sheet press down with fork.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, water and sugar and cook until berries pop.
Stir in jello, then chill.
Add remaining ingredients when mixture begins to thicken.

title: bread
directions: Scald the milk. Add sugar, salt and shortening. Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and add to milk mixture. Add flour gradually, mixing well, to make a stiff dough. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Punch down and make into loaves.
Will make 2 regular size loaves or 3 small ones.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, flour and margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and fill.
Whip Dream Whip with milk until stiff, then add vanilla and cream cheese and whip until smooth.
Add sugar.
Pour over crust and refrigerate until cool.
Top with pie filling.

title: lemon pie
directions: Bring water, sugar, butter, real lemon juice and pinch of salt to a boil in a heavy kettle or double boiler.
Once it cooks, add cornstarch, water and egg yolks.
Mix together.
Cook until thick like honey.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites in stiff peaks.
Spread on top and brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese grits souffle
directions: Cook grits according to package directions, stirring them slowly into boiling water.
Cover.
Cook slowly, stirring often. When just cooked and still hot, add grated cheese and butter. Stir until melted.
Add milk.
Cool.
Beat eggs, one at a time, and add to grits mixture.
Bake in greased casserole at 400° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: currie taylor's beef stew(slum gullion)
directions: Take any cut of beef roast.
Place in large crock-pot with water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add bouillon cube to water. Add any vegetables you want including leftovers in the fridge. Use your imagination for spices (sage, bay leaf and garlic, anything else that strikes your taste buds).
This stew never tasted exactly the same; it went according to what Dad wanted. Serve with biscuits or corn bread and honey.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add all other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Lightly mix together the potatoes, eggs, onions, salt, mustard and pepper.
Fold Miracle Whip salad dressing into mixture. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or may enjoy freshly prepared.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken whole in enough water to cover until tender. Remove from liquid to cool; retain liquid.
Bone and skin chicken and cut in bite size pieces.
Combine chicken, soup, vegetables and 2 cups of liquid in an ovenproof dish or pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in the bananas.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to banana mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christmas holly
directions: In saucepan, melt together the butter and marshmallows. Remove from heat and add vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well and stir in cornflakes.
Coat cornflakes well and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Drop red hots on top.

title: vermont graham bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in greased bread pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate the cheese.
Prepare biscuit mix as box directs.
Mix sausage and cheese into biscuit dough (hands work better than spoon).
Shape into balls the size of quarters.
Place on baking sheet and flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: swedish tea cookies
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat. Stir in 1/4 cup powdered sugar, water and vanilla. Gradually blend flour; add pecans to make pastry-like dough. Pinch off dough in teaspoon size balls or crescents. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Carefully remove. Dust with powdered sugar; cool. Dust again. Makes about 40.

title: orange frost
directions: Mix cayenne pepper with paint when painting the hull of your boat to ward off barnacles.

title: banana muffins or loaf
directions: Beat margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add bananas, milk and vanilla and beat this well.
Add egg, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir until well blended.
Add chocolate chips, nuts, dates and shredded apple.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
You can put this in either loaf pans or muffin tins.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Cover bottom of pan with sandwiches.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip.
Place another layer of sandwiches on top of that.
Cover sandwiches with Cool Whip.
Cover and freeze overnight.
Keep frozen until time to serve.

title: salmon roll sandwiches
directions: Allow cheese to come to room temperature.
Then blend with mayonnaise, onion, parsley, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Add drained, flaked salmon and adjust seasoning to taste.

title: macaroni chicken casserole
directions: Mix all and store overnight.
Put in casserole dish and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: grandma's mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl.
Bake in greased and floured cake pans (use two 8-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan) for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from all 3 cans of fruit.
Take 2 2/3 cups of juice and mix with vanilla pudding.
Bring to a boil.
Cool and pour over fruit.
Add bananas.
May also add fresh strawberries and seedless grapes.

title: tim's dirt cake
directions: 1. Grind Oreo's in blender. Set aside.
2. Cream together cream cheese, butter, and powdered sugar.
3. In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk, and coolwhip.
Blend together with cream cheese mixture.
4. In a 9x13x2 glass pan, alternate layers of crushed Ore
Oreo's and pudding with crushed cookies on top.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef and onion together and don't drain.
Don't drain beans and mix together in different bowl.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ovenproof casserole and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can reserve some bacon pieces to sprinkle on top when done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place fruit into an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Slice bread into strips and put on top of fruit.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over fruit and bread.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned homemade soap
directions: Cook out of doors in old iron laundry kettle over open fire. Stir often with a long wooden paddle.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in bacon grease until tender. Combine with eggplant, tomatoes, cornbread and egg.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in a pan over low heat; stir only until sugar is dissolved, then cook until a little tried in cold water forms a soft ball.
Beat egg whites at high speed until stiff.
Continue beating and pour half the syrup slowly over the beaten whites.
Continue beating with the rest of the syrup until it forms a hard ball when tried in cold water and cracks when hit against the side of the cup.
Add this syrup gradually to the syrup and egg mixture you are beating.
Add vanilla and beat until candy is thick enough to drop from spoon.
Place on buttered platter by spoonfuls.
Makes 40 to 50 pieces.

title: tostada pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and seasoning mix, stirring well.
Line bottom of pan (bread pan type) with 2 cups of the chips.
Spoon meat mixture over corn chips. Add remaining sauce to beans; mix well and put on top of meat. Crush remaining chips.
Put on top of beans and top with cheese. After baking for 25 minutes at 375°.
If cheese will not melt, return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: cheezy potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes with
1/2 cup butter, season with salt and pepper; add onion,
sour
cream,
soup, and grated cheese; blend. Pour into
3-quart
buttered
oblong
casserole
dish. When ready to bake,
mix
crushed
potato
chips
with 1/4 cup melted butter and spread on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and brown 15 minutes.
Serves 18.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Cream the cheese until fluffy. Add sugar and blend well.
Add vanilla and sour cream. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust and chill several hours.
Excellent topped with fresh strawberries.

title: texas "caviar"
directions: Boil black-eyed peas in salted water for 40 minutes.
Rinse with cold water.
While the peas are still warm, mix in all remaining ingredients.
Allow at least 24 hours for the flavors to mix.
The longer this sits, the better it gets.
Serve with old-fashioned saltine crackers.

title: quick ham and potatoes
directions: Brown ham in oil.
Add peeled and sliced potatoes on top in skillet; salt lightly and pepper.
Add hot water to barely cover. Cook slowly, covered, until potatoes are done.
Add enough milk to barely cover and top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Cover and simmer until cheese melts.
Thicken is necessary with cornstarch and water.
Can be baked if desired.

title: hearty beef-macaroni soup
directions: Heat oil in 5-quart soup pot.
Add meat and brown (about 5 minutes).
Reduce heat; add onions and cook approximately 5 minutes, stirring several times until soft.
Stir in flour.
Whisk in beef broth and gently scrape bottom of pot to loosen brown particles.
Stir in tomatoes, celery salt and 4 cups water.
Add macaroni, corn and peas.
Cover and boil 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 cups.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix cereal, nuts and pretzels in a large roaster pan.
Pour oil and seasonings (which have been mixed together) over cereal mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix together and store covered in refrigerator.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, blend well and add vanilla and vinegar.
Add raisins and pecans.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and cook at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm in the middle.

title: nippy bacon dip
directions: Blend cheese and mayonnaise until smooth; stir in 57 Sauce, bacon and onion.
Cover; chill.
Serve as a dip with raw vegetables, crackers or potato chips.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: pizza sandwich loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on bread.
Top with tomato slices and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place cheese slices over tomato.
Return to oven until cheese melts. Slice and serve.

title: ground beef pizza pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Press against bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Combine catsup, mushrooms, oregano and Parmesan cheese in a small bowl.
Spread over beef mixture.
Garnish with American cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Yields 4 servings.

title: delicious broccoli bread
directions: Saute onions in butter or margarine. Mix Jiffy mix with eggs, cottage cheese and broccoli. Add onion and butter. Put into oblong casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 25-30 minutes; until a nice brown on top and doesn't jiggle.

title: the greatest pancakes
directions: Mix flour, milk and salt together until smooth.
Add egg; beat well, then add melted butter.
Before cooking sprinkle over batter baking powder; fold in lightly.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then skim off foam and fry.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: l.a. (lower alabama) fajitas
directions: In a large bowl, place steak, onion, peppers and garlic.
Set aside.
In a small bowl mix 1/2 bottle of steak sauce with 1/2 bottle of Worcestershire.
Add black pepper and stir well.
Pour this mixture over steak and vegetables, tossing to coat evenly; let marinate at least 1 hour, the longer the better.
Drain marinade back into smaller bowl, adding the remainder of the steak sauce and mix well.
Place steak on grill, turning and basting frequently until done (medium to medium-rare is best).
In a skillet, place drained marinated vegetables and a small amount of the marinade; saute until tender.
Cut steak in thin strips (against grain).
Any marinade remaining can be poured over steak strips.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Beat eggs.
Add eggs, mayo, soup, and chopped onion to broccoli.
Place in baking dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and milk together.
Place in large casserole. Put chicken on top with skin side down.
Salt and pepper it.
Turn chicken once.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: wesson oil chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and roll balls in powdered sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Fry meat
without flour;
brown.
Take meat out and fry onions and
bell
peppers.
While	this
is
cooking
dissolve cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Then add pepper, garlic salt and salt
to
fried
onions
and bell peppers.	Then add cornstarch to onions and peppers; add meat and simmer.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Drain yams; set liquid aside.
Mash yams; add butter, sugar and vanilla.
If too dry, add a little liquid.
Roll into ball around a marshmallow, then roll through coconut or crushed cornflakes.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
Use as needed.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or less.

title: salsa san angelo
directions: Chop onion, peppers and garlic in small pieces.
Saute in oil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Add remainder of ingredients. Simmer over low heat 20 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: relish
directions: Mix well and put in jars; seal.
Do not heat vinegar mix.

title: homemade irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender, combine ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Serve over ice.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.

title: snickers bar cake
directions: Mix cake by directions.
Put 1/2 of batter into a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Place 3 to 4 teaspoons (according to taste) into a cup of boiling water for the best cup of hot tea you've tasted since "LuBertha was a knee baby!"

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Add buttermilk and yeast which has been dissolved in water. Stir until all flour is moist.
Roll on board dusted with flour until a nice smooth ball. Dough is ready to be used or stored in refrigerator in covered bowl for up to 2 weeks.
When ready to use, roll out as much dough as you need on floured board 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut out. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: orange pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Yields 16 servings.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat well after each.
Add sifted flour and salt alternately with the buttermilk.
Blend well.
Stir in soda, dissolved in the hot water and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: wassail(a traditional christmas punch)
directions: Heat ingredients together in crock-pot or on stove.
Keep warm.
Smells wonderful!

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Beat eggs and water; set aside.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet over medium heat.
Add green onions; stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add eggs and water mixture scramble.
Stir in rice, gently separating grains.
Add shrimp and soy sauce.
Cook, stirring, until thoroughly heated.

title: nettie's bread(spinach cornbread)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients in shallow pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350°
in a well-greased loaf pan for 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples leaving small plug in peel, skin 1 inch from top. Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Fill apples with mixture. Arrange apples in microwave dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with water.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on high 7 to 9 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix apples, celery and nuts.
Toss with mayonnaise.
Arrange on lettuce leaves, if desired. Garnish with walnut halves and cherries.
Yields 4 servings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain all fruit completely.
Cream Cool Whip and cream cheese together.
Add other ingredients and mix well on medium speed. Pour into baked pie crust and chill for 1 hour.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Put peaches cut side down in crust.
Mix sugar & cornstarch. Sprinkle over peaches.
Pour cream over all.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake 1 hour until peaches are tender and cream has thickened.

title: granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except chocolate chips until moistened.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Press mixture evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until center is set, 15 to 17 minutes.

title: meff's macaroni and cheese
directions: Add macaroni to boiling water.
Boil only two to three minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Meanwhile, finely cut Cracker Barrel extra sharp cheese and add another mild cheese like Monterey Jack.
Mix cold macaroni into cheese.
Then add enough scalding milk to cover macaroni and cheese.
Should be a little more than a half gallon of milk.
Melt the margarine in milk, along with salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni and cheese.
Put in oven at 250° for three hours.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients; add to the creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Mix just until combined.
Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yield: about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: saleen's christmas punch
directions: Mix with love. Serve to your family.

title: yummie goulash
directions: Wash potatoes; cut up in salad cubes.
Set aside.
Cut bacon up in 1-inch pieces; fry.
Take bacon up; leave drippings.
Put potatoes in drippings and fry until done.
Put bacon back in potatoes; add pork and beans.
Let simmer for 10 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Fry garlic and onion until transparent.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and cover and bake for about 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.
Put in a foil pan, casserole dish or bean pot.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Slice rolls and put ham and cheese on them.
Place in pan. Then mix spices with margarine (melted).
Spoon over top of biscuits and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: franklin nut cake(white fruit cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs.
Add 3 cups of the flour (sifted with the baking powder and salt).
Mix remaining flour with cherries, pineapple and broken nuts.
Stir into batter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into tube pan that has been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Let cool in pan.

title: curried chicken 'n' broccoli
directions: Place the broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish. Top with the chicken.

title: low-fat oven baked chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic powder and salt.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Roll in cheese and then in flakes or crumbs. Place on baking dish sprayed with Pam.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together the cauliflower, bacon and cheese.
Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Combine mixtures immediately before serving.

title: darb's daddy's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck in a very small amount of oil and then add the onion and brown the two together.
Then add tomato sauce and chili beans and stir well.
Next, add the boiling water, stirring the chili real good.
Then add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over medium to high heat, making sure it doesn't stick.
Cook about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Cook pork chops until brown on both sides.
Mix all other ingredients, except vegetables and potatoes.
Pour over top of pork chops.
Heat to boiling.
Turn down heat and add potatoes.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook about 10 minutes more.

title: jello "poke" cake
directions: Bake any white cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
While cake is baking, combine remaining ingredients.
Set aside.
Do not put jello into refrigerator.
When cake is cool, take meat fork and "poke" holes in cake.
Pour jello over cake; frost.
This cake should be refrigerated.
Cool Whip makes a great topping.

title: chicken 'n dressing casserole
directions: Pressure cook or boil chicken in small amount of water (canned chicken can be substituted).

title: hanky panky
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage together.
Drain.
Add cheese, garlic salt, worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Stir until cheese melts.
Place mixture on party rye and freeze on cookie sheets. Once frozen, store in freezer bags until ready to use.
To cook, place frozen appetizers on cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes in a 350 degree preheated oven.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage into large casserole and top with everything. Add water.
Cover and bake about 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Stir often; add water if needed.

title: microwave sesame chicken
directions: Combine brown sugar, soy sauce, dry sherry, sesame oil, ginger root, black pepper, cayenne pepper and garlic in 2-quart microwave casserole dish.
Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips and add to marinade.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1/2 hours. Drain chicken; reserve 1/4 cup marinade.
Combine reserved marinade and cornstarch.
Stir in chicken.
Cover again with plastic wrap (vent 1 corner).
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Uncover and stir in red pepper and scallions.
Re-cover (vent corner).
Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes until chicken is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Re-cover with plastic wrap; let stand 1 minute.
Serve with rice. Serves 4.

title: greens and beans
directions: Cut and wash greens.
Boil water.
Drop in greens; cook until tender and drain.
Saute garlic in oil.
Add greens and simmer. Add beans and juice, salt and black pepper.
A little crushed red pepper adds flavor.

title: pecan swirl pudding cake(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Combine rest of the ingredients in large bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and nut mix.
Keep away from sides of pan.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Do not underbake. Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, beating 1 at a time.
Mix 2 cups flour, beating after each cup.
Add whipping cream and then last cup of flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake is done.
Test with a toothpick.
Bake cake in a 10-inch cake pan.

title: shrimp with prosciutto
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Cut Prosciutto into 12 equal pieces. Saute butter, garlic and white wine.
Place shrimp in an ovensafe glass pan and cover each shrimp with a piece of Prosciutto.
Pour butter sauce over shrimp and sprinkle Mozzarella over entire pan. Bake at 350° until shrimp are cooked.
Serves 3 to 4 as an appetizer.

title: honey-parmesan dressing
directions: Blend onion and 3/4 cup mayonnaise.
Add honey.
Blend until mixed well.
Add other mayonnaise, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Heat half the fat in iron pan; crumble meat in and cook until slightly brown, stirring to cook well.
Use other fats to cook onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic to yellow stage; do not brown.
Add this to meat mixture, also tomatoes, tomato sauce and other seasonings and simmer for 1 hour; remove from heat, add cheese and mix well.
Have spaghetti cooked and fill casserole, using alternate layers of spaghetti and sauce; top with a small amount of cheese and heat until it bubbles.
You may prefer to serve on platter, pour sauce over and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pork chops creole
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops; pour off drippings. Sprinkle chops with pepper; place slice of onion and green pepper on each. Pour tomato rice soup and water over chops. Sprinkle with whole thyme. Cover; cook 45 minutes over low heat. Stir now and then. Makes 6 servings.

title: nikki's french toast
directions: First, cook the brown sugar and corn syrup on medium heat. Stir until dissolved. Pour caramel mixture in baking dish.
Coat entire bottom of dish.
Place the bread in dish.
Beat eggs and pour on top of bread.
Cover.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve flipped over with caramel side up.

title: judthra
directions: Cook beans in water, salt and pepper for 20 to 25 minutes. Saute onion in oleo until brown.
Add to beans.
Add rice.
Add more water if needed.
Bring to boiling.
Turn fire to low.
Cook until rice is done.

title: scottish mustard butter
directions: Cream butter; add mustard, parsley and squeeze of lemon. Spoon butter onto square of foil.
Shape into fat roll and twist ends up like a party cracker.
Chill until firm.

title: spanish rice and pork chops
directions: Slightly brown chops in shortening in Dutch oven or heavy pot. Remove from fire and place half of the chops in bottom of the pan.
Add rice and then onion rings.
Add tomatoes and remaining chops.
Season to taste.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all the
ingredients
and boil 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: jelly filled donuts
directions: Deep-fry biscuits in Crisco oil.
Turn; both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Punch hole in side.
Spoon in Simply Fruit jelly. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Add baking powder in applesauce until foamy.
Add to other mixture.
Mix well.
Now add raisins and nuts.
Beat until blended.
Bake in well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
